class=3D\"menu-1187 active-trail first =\nactive\"><a href=3D\"/about-nygb\" title=3D\"\" class=3D\"active-trail active\">Ab=\nout the NYG&amp;B</a></li>=0A<li class=3D\"menu-1191\"><a =0A         <h1 clas=\ns=3D\"title\" id=3D\"page-title\">=0A                      About the NYG&amp;B =\n          \t\t</h1>=0A       =0A                  <div class=3D\"region region=\n-content\">=0A    <div id=3D\"block-system-main\" class=3D\"block block-system\">=\n=0A=0A    =0A  <div class=3D\"content\">=0A    <div id=3D\"node-13\" class=3D\"n=\node node-page clearfix\" about=3D\"/about-nygb\" typeof=3D\"foaf:Document\">=0A=\n=0A  =0A      =0A  =0A  <div class=3D\"content\">=0A    <span class=3D\"print-=\nlink\"><span class=3D\"print_html\"><a href=3D\"http://newyorkfamilyhistory.org=\n/print/13\" title=3D\"Display a printer-friendly version of this page.\" class=\n=3D\"print-page\" onclick=3D\"window.open(this.href); return false\" rel=3D\"nof=\nollow\"><img class=3D\"print-icon print-icon-margin\" typeof=3D\"foaf:Image\" sr=\nc=3D\"http://newyorkfamilyhistory.org/sites/all/modules/print/icons/print_ic=\non.gif\" alt=3D\"Printer-friendly version\" title=3D\"Printer-friendly version\"=\n />Printer-friendly version</a></span></span><div class=3D\"field field-name=\n-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden\"><div class=3D\"field-=\nitems\"><div class=3D\"field-item even\" property=3D\"content:encoded\"><p class=\n=3D\"rtecenter\">=0A\t<img alt=3D\"\" src=3D\"/sites/default/files/images/9.jpg\" =\nstyle=3D\"width: 595px; height: 150px;\" /></p>=0A<h2>=0A\tThe NYG&amp;B is th=\ne most authoritative source for research on New York families and families =\nwith New York connections. Founded in 1869, it is the largest genealogical =\nsociety in New York and the only one that is state-wide. The NYG&amp;B enga=\nges with the dynamic, fast growing, rapidly changing field of family histor=\ny through accurate, thorough research and the highest standards of scholars=\nhip.</h2>=0A<h3>=0A\tOur Mission</h3>=0A<p>=0A\tThe mission of the NYG&amp;B =\nis to help people of all backgrounds discover their family histories (espec=\nially those aspects of their family histories which relate to New York City=\n, State, and region) and find meaning by placing their own family's experie=\nnce into the broader context of American history.=C2=A0</p>=0A<p>=0A\tWe bel=\nieve that all families are important, all family histories are worthy of pr=\neservation, and all families are essential parts of a larger historical nar=\nrative. =C2=A0We believe that linking families to the history of the nation=\n is profoundly meaningful and is powerfully beneficial on many levels.</p>=\n=0A<h3>=0A\tParticipation and Operations</h3>=0A<p>=0A\tThe NYG&amp;B is a me=\nmbership organization, and we welcome all people who are curious about rese=\narching their family histories. <a href=3D\"/join\" target=3D\"_self\">Learn mo=\nre</a> about becoming a member. =C2=A0We are a not-for-profit organization =\nwith tax exempt status, and <a href=3D\"/giving-opportunities\" target=3D\"_se=\nlf\">gifts</a> to the NYG&amp;B are tax deductible. We have a headquarters o=\nffice in New York City with a professional staff and a dedicated group of v=\nolunteers. We are governed by a distinguished Board of Trustees who serve v=\noluntarily and contribute generously.</p>=0A<p>=0A\tWe are supported mainly =\nby membership dues; annual gifts from members and trustees; and bequests.=\n=C2=A0 <a href=3D\"/giving-opportunities\">Learn more</a> about supporting th=\ne NYG&amp;B.</p>=0A<h3>=0A\tAreas of Endeavor</h3>=0A<p>=0A\tWe focus on thre=\ne areas:</p>=0A<ul><li>=0A<p>=0A\t\t\t<strong>Publications</strong>. We publis=\nh two quarterly journals, <a href=3D\"/nygbr\" target=3D\"_self\"><em>The Recor=\nd</em></a> and <a href=3D\"/research\" target=3D\"_self\"><em>The New York Rese=\narcher</em></a>. Subscriptions are benefits of membership.</p>=0A</li>=0A</=\nul><ul><li>=0A<p>=0A\t\t\t<strong>Educational Programming. </strong>We produce=\n a broad range of educational programming, and we are the lead organization=\n developing <a href=3D\"/history-school\" target=3D\"_self\">The New York Famil=\ny History School</a>. We also partner with the New York Public Library to d=\nevelop educational programs for students, teachers, and patrons of the bran=\nch library system in New York City.</p>=0A</li>=0A</ul><ul><li>=0A<p>=0A\t\t\t=\n<strong>Website. </strong>This website contains extensive resources that be=\nnefit people researching families connected to New York State. Resources in=\nclude guides to exploring resources relevant to New York, as well as primar=\ny materials that are unique to this site. Full access to the website is a b=\nenefit of <a href=3D\"/join\">membership</a>.</p>=0A</li>=0A</ul><p>=0A\t<br />=\n=0A\t=C2=A0</p>=0A</div></div></div>  </div>=0A=0A  =0A  =0A</div>=0A  </div>=\n=0A</div>=0A  </div>=0A      </article>=0A    </div>=0A    <footer>=0A     =\n <nav>=0A        <ul>=0A          <li><a href=3D\"/privacy\">Privacy</a></li>=\n=0A          <li><a href=3D\"/service-terms\">Terms of Service</a></li>=0A   =\n       <li><a href=3D\"/advertising\">Advertising</a></li>=0A          <li><a=\n href=3D\"/press\">Press Room</a></li>=0A          <li><a href=3D\"http://www.=\nironpaper.com\">Web Design</a></li>=0A        </ul>=0A        <a href=3D\"htt=\np://www.facebook.com/pages/The-New-York-Genealogical-Biographical-Society/1=\n66498443372313\" rel=3D\"nofollow\"  target=3D\"_blank\"><img src=3D\"/sites/all/=\nthemes/nygbs/images/content-img/icon-facebook.png\" alt=3D\"Facebook page\"  b=\norder=3D\"0\" /></a>=0A            <a href=3D\"http://twitter.com/#!/nyfamilyh=\nistory\" rel=3D\"nofollow\" target=3D\"_blank\"><img src=3D\"/sites/all/themes/ny=\ngbs/images/content-img/icon-twitter.png\" alt=3D\"Twitter page\"  border=3D\"0\"=\n /></a>=0A            <a href=3D\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/nygbs/\" rel=\n=3D\"nofollow\"  target=3D\"_blank\"><img src=3D\"/sites/all/themes/nygbs/images=\n/content-img/icon-flickr.png\" alt=3D\"Flickr page\"  border=3D\"0\" /></a>=0A  =\n    </nav>=0A     <div id=3D\"copyright\">=0A        New York Genealogical &a=\nmp; First opened in 1863,=\n it is located in the Bronx at Webster  Avenue &amp; East 233rd Street. It =\nis the final home of many of New York  City's historic figures such as Admi=\nral David G. Farragut; author  Herman Melville; abolitionist and women's ri=\nghts activist Elizabeth Cady  Stanton; and journalist Joseph Pulitzer.=C2=\n=A0</p></div></div></div></div><div class=3D\"field field-name-field-datetim=\ne field-type-datetime field-label-inline clearfix\"><div class=3D\"field-labe=\nl\">When:&nbsp;</div><div class=3D\"field-items\"><div class=3D\"field-item eve=\nn\"><span class=3D\"date-display-single\">Saturday, September 15, 2012 - Join the people who know New York research b=\nest for three days of research and genealogical camaraderie.</p>=0A<p>Progr=\nam includes:</p></div></div></div><div class=3D\"field field-name-field-date=\ntime field-type-datetime field-label-inline clearfix\"><div class=3D\"field-l=\nabel\">When:&nbsp;</div><div class=3D\"field-items\"><div class=3D\"field-item =\neven\"><span class=3D\"date-display-start\">Thursday, November 1, 2012 - 9:00a=\nm</span><span class=3D\"date-display-separator\"> - </span><span class=3D\"dat=\ne-display-end\">Saturday, November 3, 2012 - 9:00pm</span></div></div></div>=\n<div class=3D\"field field-name-field-venue field-type-text field-label-inli=\nne clearfix\"><div class=3D\"field-label\">Venue:&nbsp;</div><div class=3D\"fie=\nld-items\"><div class=3D\"field-item even\">Hotel Albany, NY State Archives, N=\nY State Library and the City of Albany!</div></div></div><div class=3D\"fiel=\nd field-name-field-sponsor field-type-text field-label-inline clearfix\"><di=\nv class=3D\"field-label\">Sponsor:&nbsp;</div><div class=3D\"field-items\"><div=\n class=3D\"field-item even\">The New York Genealogical & Biographical Society=\n</div></div></div>  </div>=0A=0A  <ul class=3D\"links inline\"><li class=3D\"n=\node-readmore first last\"><a href=3D\"/albany2012\" rel=3D\"tag\" title=3D\"Resea=\nrch in Albany 2012\">Read more<span class=3D\"element-invisible\"> about Resea=\nrch in Albany 2012</span></a></li>=0A</ul>=0A  =0A</div>=0A  </div>=0A  <di=\nv class=3D\"views-row views-row-5 views-row-odd\">=0A    <div id=3D\"node-518\"=\n class=3D\"node node-events node-teaser clearfix\" about=3D\"/heraldrywine\" ty=\npeof=3D\"sioc:Item foaf:Document\">=0A=0A  =0A        <h2 property=3D\"dc:titl=\ne\" datatype=3D\"\"><a href=3D\"/heraldrywine\">Heraldry on Wine Labels &amp; Wi=\nne Tasting</a></h2>=0A    =0A  =0A  <div class=3D\"content\">=0A    <div clas=\ns=3D\"field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden\"=\n><div class=3D\"field-items\"><div class=3D\"field-item even\" property=3D\"cont=\nent:encoded\"><p>The Heraldry Committee members will select of a number of w=\nine bottle labels displaying a coat of arms. Then there will be a presentat=\nion on the history of those arms accompanied by a tasting of the wines in q=\nuestion. This program may occur on a different date in November. Please che=\nck back later in 2012 for a definitive date.    The program is free but res=\nervations are necessary as capacity is limited.  Please call 212-755-8532 x=\n211 for reservations.</p>=0A</div></div></div><div class=3D\"field field-nam=\ne-field-datetime field-type-datetime field-label-inline clearfix\"><div clas=\ns=3D\"field-label\">When:&nbsp;</div><div class=3D\"field-items\"><div class=3D=\n\"field-item even\"><span class=3D\"date-display-single\">Monday, November 12, =\n2012 - <span class=3D\"date-display-start\">6:00pm</span><span class=3D\"date-=\ndisplay-separator\"> - </span><span class=3D\"date-display-end\">8:00pm</span>=\n</span></div></div></div><div class=3D\"field field-name-field-venue field-t=\nype-text field-label-inline clearfix\"><div class=3D\"field-label\">Venue:&nbs=\np;</div><div class=3D\"field-items\"><div class=3D\"field-item even\">New York =\nGenealogical and Biographical Society</div></div></div><div class=3D\"field =\nfield-name-field-sponsor field-type-text field-label-inline clearfix\"><div =\nclass=3D\"field-label\">Sponsor:&nbsp;</div><div class=3D\"field-items\"><div c=\nlass=3D\"field-item even\">Heraldry Committee of the NYG&B</div></div></div> =\n </div>=0A=0A  <ul class=3D\"links inline\"><li class=3D\"node-readmore first =\nlast\"><a href=3D\"/heraldrywine\" rel=3D\"tag\" title=3D\"Heraldry on Wine Label=\ns &amp; Wine Tasting\">Read more<span class=3D\"element-invisible\"> about Her=\naldry on Wine Labels &amp; Wine Tasting</span></a></li>=0A</ul>=0A  =0A</di=\nv>=0A  </div>=0A  <div class=3D\"views-row views-row-6 views-row-even views-=\nrow-last\">=0A    <div id=3D\"node-517\" class=3D\"node node-events node-teaser=\n clearfix\" about=3D\"/heraldrycoat\" typeof=3D\"sioc:Item foaf:Document\">=0A=\n=0A  =0A        <h2 property=3D\"dc:title\" datatype=3D\"\"><a href=3D\"/heraldr=\nycoat\">Differentiating a Logo from a Coat of Arms</a></h2>=0A    =0A  =0A  =\n<div class=3D\"content\">=0A    <div class=3D\"field field-name-body field-typ=\ne-text-with-summary field-label-hidden\"><div class=3D\"field-items\"><div cla=\nss=3D\"field-item even\" property=3D\"content:encoded\"><p>Cathy Bursey-Sabouri=\nn, Fraser Herald of the Canadian Heraldic Authority, will speak on the dist=\ninction between a logo and a coat of arms.  Ms. Bursey-Sabourin has been Fr=\naser Herald at the Canadian Heraldic Authority in Ottawa since 1989.  She i=\ns the principal artist of the Authority.  Bursey-Sabourin has been responsi=\nble for the paintings made for the arms of the last five Governors General =\nof Canada and the Coat of arms of Canada.     The program is free but reser=\nvations are necessary as capacity is limited. Please call 212-755-8532 x211=\n for reservations.</p>=0A</div></div></div><div class=3D\"field field-name-f=\nield-datetime field-type-datetime field-label-inline clearfix\"><div class=3D\"menu-501 last\"><a href=3D\"/nyfhsdirector=\ns\">Board of Advisors</a></li>=0A</ul>          </div> <!-- /#secondary-menu=\n -->=0A                =0A                =0A      </aside>=0A            <=\narticle class=3D\"\">      =0A                =0A         <h1 class=3D\"title\"=\n id=3D\"page-title\">=0A                      The New York Family History Sch=\nool           \t\t</h1>=0A       =0A                  <div class=3D\"region re=\ngion-content\">=0A    <div id=3D\"block-system-main\" class=3D\"block block-sys=\ntem\">=0A=0A    =0A  <div class=3D\"content\">=0A    <div id=3D\"node-3\" class=\n=3D\"node node-page clearfix\" about=3D\"/history-school\" typeof=3D\"foaf:Docum=\nent\">=0A=0A  =0A      =0A  =0A  <div class=3D\"content\">=0A    <span class=\n=3D\"print-link\"><span class=3D\"print_html\"><a href=3D\"http://newyorkfamilyh=\nistory.org/print/3\" title=3D\"Display a printer-friendly version of this pag=\ne.\" class=3D\"print-page\" onclick=3D\"window.open(this.href); return false\" r=\nel=3D\"nofollow\"><img class=3D\"print-icon print-icon-margin\" typeof=3D\"foaf:=\nImage\" src=3D\"http://newyorkfamilyhistory.org/sites/all/modules/print/icons=\n/print_icon.gif\" alt=3D\"Printer-friendly version\" title=3D\"Printer-friendly=\n version\" />Printer-friendly version</a></span></span><div class=3D\"field f=\nield-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden\"><div class=\n=3D\"field-items\"><div class=3D\"field-item even\" property=3D\"content:encoded=\n\"><h2>=0A\t<span>The goal of the New York Family History School=E2=84=A2 (NY=\nFHS), created in 2010, is to unite the genealogical community in New York S=\ntate. Its purpose is to benefit people doing research and to help genealogi=\ncal organizations serve researchers more effectively.=C2=A0=C2=A0 </span></=\nh2>=0A<h2>=0A\t<span>The New York Genealogical and Biographical Society, the=\n Milstein Division of the New York Public Library, and the National Archive=\ns in New York City were the founding partners.</span></h2>=0A<p class=3D\"rt=\necenter\">=0A\t<a href=3D\"http://www.newyorkfamilyhistory.org/\"><img alt=3D\"\"=\n src=3D\"/sites/default/files/images/NYGB color.jpg\" style=3D\"width: 172px; =\nheight: 90px;\" /></a><a href=3D\"http://www.nypl.org/\"><img alt=3D\"\" src=3D\"=\n/sites/default/files/images/New-York-Public-Library-logo.jpg\" style=3D\"widt=\nh: 180px; height: 93px;\" /></a><a href=3D\"http://www.archives.gov/northeast=\n/nyc/\"><img alt=3D\"\" src=3D\"/sites/default/files/images/174540_182027198778=\n_7177518_n(2).jpg\" style=3D\"width: 188px; height: 94px;\" /></a></p>=0A<h3>=\n=0A\tOrigins and Mission</h3>=0A<p>=0A\tThe New York Family History School be=\ngan its work by focusing on three goals:</p>=0A<ul><li>=0A<p>=0A\t\t\tTo creat=\ne high quality educational programming that helps people do better family h=\nistory research.</p>=0A</li>=0A<li>=0A<p>=0A\t\t\tTo identify and create aware=\nness of educational programming offered by other genealogical organizations=\n in New York State.</p>=0A</li>=0A<li>=0A<p>=0A\t\t\tTo convene leaders of the=\n genealogical community for the purpose of creating strategy and developing=\n and executing larger scale projects.=C2=A0</p>=0A</li>=0A</ul><p>=0A\tOur m=\nission is to provide people with practical skills and know-how so they can =\ndo better family history research. We focus on families with connections to=\n New York City, State, and region but the programs have very general applic=\nability.</p>=0A<p>=0A\tWe want to help people like you work smarter and fast=\ner and gain even more personal fulfillment as you explore your own family h=\nistory.=C2=A0 This is important because the purpose of genealogy=C2=A0 is t=\no connect with our families, our communities, and our places in American hi=\nstory, regardless of the length of our families' experiences in America or =\nour stations in life.</p>=0A<h3>=0A\tActivity &amp; Programs</h3>=0A<p>=0A\tT=\nhe NYFHS establishes a hub for genealogy and family history, benefiting the=\n entire genealogy and family history community in New York. It is being dev=\neloped by the staff of the NYG&amp;B, which is underwriting the start-up co=\nsts as a service to the field, while it depends on the support of many peop=\nle affiliated with many other organizations.</p>=0A<p>=0A\tAt the present ti=\nme, we are working to build a consolidated educational programs calendar un=\niting the work of genealogical societies throughout New York State. We add =\ncontinuously to a calendar of events region-wide that you can see in one pl=\nace. If you are aware of programs that would benefit from listing here, ple=\nase contact <a href=3D\"mailto:webmaster@nygbs.org\">webmaster@nygbs.org</a>.=\n</p>=0A<p>=0A\tView a chronologiical <a href=3D\"/nyfhs-programs\">list of pro=\ngrams</a> currently in the calendar. This list <em>includes</em> the progra=\nms of the NYG&amp;B.</p>=0A<p>=0A\tWe have created as complete and accurate =\na list as possible of <a href=3D\"/societiesguide\">functioning genealogical =\norganizations</a> in the New York region with links to the relevant web sit=\nes. We add continuously to a calendar of events region-wide that you can se=\ne in one place.</p>=0A<h3>=0A\tThe Future</h3>=0A<p>=0A\tThe NYFHS has an amb=\nitious growth path, and as it forms we are open to new ideas and feedback. =\nWe do intend to reach bigger, more diverse audiences; to offer access to mo=\nre extensive program offerings; and we are exploring ideas for advanced stu=\ndy.</p>=0A<p>=0A\tWe are working to gain qualified partners who offer public=\n programs of quality.</p>=0A<p>=0A\tOur ambitious plans include the developm=\nent of online courses, additional partnerships with other large organizatio=\nns, and development of programs jointly sponsored by multiple groups, such =\nas The New York Family History Fair<sup>TM</sup>.</p>=0A<p>=0A\t<a class=3D\"=\nbtn-link\" href=3D\"/nyfhs-programs\">View NYFHS Programs</a></p>=0A<p>=0A\t=C2=\n=A0</p>=0A</div></div></div>  </div>=0A=0A  =0A  =0A</div>=0A  </div>=0A</d=\niv>=0A  </div>=0A      </article>=0A    </div>=0A    <footer>=0A      <nav>=\n=0A        <ul>=0A          <li><a href=3D\"/privacy\">Privacy</a></li>=0A   =\n       <li><a href=3D\"/service-terms\">Terms of Service</a></li>=0A         =\n <li><a href=3D\"/advertising\">Advertising</a></li>=0A          <li><a href=\n=3D\"/press\">Press Room</a></li>=0A          <li><a href=3D\"http://www.ironp=\naper.com\">Web Design</a></li>=0A        </ul>=0A        <a href=3D\"http://w=\nww.facebook.com/pages/The-New-York-Genealogical-Biographical-Society/166498=\n443372313\" rel=3D\"nofollow\"  target=3D\"_blank\"><img src=3D\"/sites/all/theme=\ns/nygbs/images/content-img/icon-facebook.png\" alt=3D\"Facebook page\"  border=\n=3D\"0\" /></a>=0A            <a href=3D\"http://twitter.com/#!/nyfamilyhistor=\ny\" rel=3D\"nofollow\" target=3D\"_blank\"><img src=3D\"/sites/all/themes/nygbs/i=\nmages/content-img/icon-twitter.png\" alt=3D\"Twitter page\"  border=3D\"0\" /></=\na>=0A            <a href=3D\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/nygbs/\" rel=3D\"nof=\nollow\"  target=3D\"_blank\"><img src=3D\"/sites/all/themes/nygbs/images/conten=\nt-img/icon-flickr.png\" alt=3D\"Flickr page\"  border=3D\"0\" /></a>=0A      </n=\nav>=0A     <div id=3D\"copyright\">=0A        New York Genealogical &amp; <!-- /#=\nsecondary-menu -->=0A                =0A                =0A      </aside>=\n=0A            <article class=3D\"\">      =0A                =0A         <h1=\n class=3D\"title\" id=3D\"page-title\">=0A                      Join the NYG&am=\np;B           \t\t</h1>=0A       =0A                  <div class=3D\"region re=\ngion-content\">=0A    <div id=3D\"block-system-main\" class=3D\"block block-sys=\ntem\">=0A=0A    =0A  <div class=3D\"content\">=0A    <div id=3D\"node-17\" class=\n=3D\"node node-page clearfix\" about=3D\"/join\" typeof=3D\"foaf:Document\">=0A=\n=0A  =0A      =0A  =0A  <div class=3D\"content\">=0A    <span class=3D\"print-=\nlink\"><span class=3D\"print_html\"><a href=3D\"http://newyorkfamilyhistory.org=\n/print/17\" title=3D\"Display a printer-friendly version of this page.\" class=\n=3D\"print-page\" onclick=3D\"window.open(this.href); return false\" rel=3D\"nof=\nollow\"><img class=3D\"print-icon print-icon-margin\" typeof=3D\"foaf:Image\" sr=\nc=3D\"http://newyorkfamilyhistory.org/sites/all/modules/print/icons/print_ic=\non.gif\" alt=3D\"Printer-friendly version\" title=3D\"Printer-friendly version\"=\n />Printer-friendly version</a></span></span><div class=3D\"field field-name=\n-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden\"><div class=3D\"field-=\nitems\"><div class=3D\"field-item even\" property=3D\"content:encoded\"><p>=0A\t<=\nimg alt=3D\"\" src=3D\"/sites/default/files/images/8[1](1).jpg\" style=3D\"width=\n: 621px; height: 195px\" /></p>=0A<h2>=0A\tMembership in the NYG&amp;B is for=\n you if you have New York connections and want to learn more about your fam=\nily history, or if you simply enjoy the community of people who share your =\ninterests.</h2>=0A<div>=0A\t<a class=3D\"btn-link\" href=3D\"https://newyorkfam=\nilyhistory.myshopify.com/collections/memberships\">Join/Renew Membership</a>=\n</div>=0A<p>=0A\tOur purpose is to help you =E2=80=94 through the discovery =\nof your family history =E2=80=94 connect with your extended family, your co=\nmmunity, and your culture and heritage. And when you can link your family=\n=E2=80=99s experience with events, people, and ideas from the past, you bui=\nld a personal connection with American history.</p>=0A<p>=0A\tThe NYG&amp;B,=\n founded in 1869, continually evolves and is a contemporary, forward-lookin=\ng organization that welcomes everyone and embraces technology and innovatio=\nn. As the hub of New York=E2=80=99s genealogical community, the NYG&amp;B p=\nartners with repositories and membership societies throughout the state and=\n region to help our members tap the most important resources available. Our=\n focus is education: we want to help you advance your research skills, expa=\nnd your knowledge, and enrich your life. We do this through programs with t=\nhe top speakers in the field; publications with articles by leading experts=\n; and exclusive online resources for members. Your membership dues will bri=\nng you many tangible benefits plus the satisfaction that comes from helping=\n others succeed. Join us.</p>=0A</div></div></div>  </div>=0A=0A  =0A  =0A<=\n/div>=0A  </div>=0A</div>=0A  </div>=0A      </article>=0A    </div>=0A    =\n<footer>=0A      <nav>=0A        <ul>=0A          <li><a href=3D\"/privacy\">=\nPrivacy</a></li>=0A          <li><a href=3D\"/service-terms\">Terms of Servic=\ne</a></li>=0A          <li><a href=3D\"/advertising\">Advertising</a></li>=0A=\n          <li><a href=3D\"/press\">Press Room</a></li>=0A          <li><a hre=\nf=3D\"http://www.ironpaper.com\">Web Design</a></li>=0A        </ul>=0A      =\n  <a href=3D\"http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-New-York-Genealogical-Biogra=\nphical-Society/166498443372313\" rel=3D\"nofollow\"  target=3D\"_blank\"><img sr=\nc=3D\"/sites/all/themes/nygbs/images/content-img/icon-facebook.png\" alt=3D\"F=\nacebook page\"  border=3D\"0\" /></a>=0A            <a href=3D\"http://twitter.=\ncom/#!/nyfamilyhistory\" rel=3D\"nofollow\" target=3D\"_blank\"><img src=3D\"/sit=\nes/all/themes/nygbs/images/content-img/icon-twitter.png\" alt=3D\"Twitter pag=\ne\"  border=3D\"0\" /></a>=0A            <a href=3D\"http://www.flickr.com/phot=\nos/nygbs/\" rel=3D\"nofollow\"  target=3D\"_blank\"><img src=3D\"/sites/all/theme=\ns/nygbs/images/content-img/icon-flickr.png\" alt=3D\"Flickr page\"  border=3D\"=\n0\" /></a>=0A      </nav>=0A     <div id=3D\"copyright\">=0A        New York G=\nenealogical &amp; Some assignments require your presence on-site at the NYG&amp;=\nB during business hours while others can be accomplished in your own home o=\nn your own schedule.</p>=0A<p>Whether you prefer to work in a group or inde=\npendently; whether you have professional skills you wish to lend, to acquir=\ne, or to hone; whether you love technology or don't, there is room for you =\nto make a contribution that brings the reward of knowing that you are helpi=\nng fellow NYG&amp;B members who share your joy in genealogy.</p>=0A<h3>Join=\n Our Volunteer Team</h3>=0A<p>To apply for a volunteer position please send=\n an email and resume, if one is available, to <a href=3D\"mailto:volunteer@n=\nygbs.org\">volunteer@nygbs.org</a>. href=3D\"/webstercemetery\">Walking To=\nur: Woodlawn Cemetery </a></h2>=0A    =0A  =0A  <div class=3D\"content\">=0A =\n   <div class=3D\"field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-l=\nabel-hidden\"><div class=3D\"field-items\"><div class=3D\"field-item even\" prop=\nerty=3D\"content:encoded\"><div>=0A<p>The NYG&amp;B is hosting a walking tour=\n of beautiful Woodlawn  Cemetery. First opened in 1863, it is located in th=\ne Bronx at Webster  Avenue &amp; East 233rd Street. It is the final home of=\n many of New York  City's historic figures such as Admiral David G. Farragu=\nt; author  Herman Melville; abolitionist and women's rights activist Elizab=\neth Cady  Stanton; and journalist Joseph Pulitzer.=C2=A0</p></div></div></d=\niv></div><div class=3D\"field field-name-field-datetime field-type-datetime =\nfield-label-inline clearfix\"><div class=3D\"field-label\">When:&nbsp;</div><d=\niv class=3D\"field-items\"><div class=3D\"field-item even\"><span class=3D\"date=\n-display-single\">Saturday, September 15, 2012 - <span class=3D\"date-display=\n-start\">11:00am</span><span class=3D\"date-display-separator\"> - </span><spa=\nn class=3D\"date-display-end\">1:30pm</span></span></div></div></div><div cla=\nss=3D\"field field-name-field-venue field-type-text field-label-inline clear=\nfix\"><div class=3D\"field-label\">Venue:&nbsp;</div><div class=3D\"field-items=\n\"><div class=3D\"field-item even\">Woodlawn Cemetery - Webster Avenue & East =\n233rd Street </div></div></div><div class=3D\"field field-name-field-sponsor=\n field-type-text field-label-inline clearfix\"><div class=3D\"field-label\">Sp=\nonsor:&nbsp;</div><div class=3D\"field-items\"><div class=3D\"field-item even\"=\n>The New York Genealogical & Biographical Society</div></div></div>  </div>=\n=0A=0A  <ul class=3D\"links inline\"><li class=3D\"node-readmore first last\"><=\na href=3D\"/webstercemetery\" rel=3D\"tag\" title=3D\"Walking Tour: Woodlawn Cem=\netery \">Read more<span class=3D\"element-invisible\"> about Walking Tour: Woo=\ndlawn Cemetery </span></a></li>=0A</ul>=0A  =0A</div>=0A  </div>=0A  <div c=\nlass=3D\"views-row views-row-2 views-row-even\">=0A    <div id=3D\"node-585\" c=\nlass=3D\"node node-events node-teaser clearfix\" about=3D\"/heraldryUSPresiden=\nts\" typeof=3D\"sioc:Item foaf:Document\">=0A=0A  =0A        <h2 property=3D\"d=\nc:title\" datatype=3D\"\"><a href=3D\"/heraldryUSPresidents\">Learn About the He=\nraldry of American Presidents </a></h2>=0A    =0A  =0A  <div class=3D\"conte=\nnt\">=0A    <div class=3D\"field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary=\n field-label-hidden\"><div class=3D\"field-items\"><div class=3D\"field-item ev=\nen\" property=3D\"content:encoded\"><div>Take a break from the frenzy of elect=\nion year politics and hear about the hearldry of American presidents - both=\n hereditary arms of early U.S. presidents and also more recently granted ar=\nms. Joseph McMillian will discuss the topic on Monday, September 17th at th=\ne NYG&amp;B's headquarters on West 44th St., followed by traditional refres=\nhments sponsored by the Heraldry Committee of the NYG&amp;B (John Shannon, =\nchairman). This will cover both hereditary arms of early US p=\nresidents and also more recent granted arms.  Mr. McMillan is a governor-at=\n-large of the American College of Heraldry.  A career civil servant with ov=\ner 28 years of service in the Department of Defense, he is a senior researc=\nh fellow at the Institute for National Strategic Studies.=C2=A0</p>=0A<p>=\n=C2=A0</p>=0A<p>The program is free but reservations are necessary as capac=\nity is limited.</p>=0A<p>Please call 212-755-8532 x211 for reservations. =\n=C2=A0</p>=0A</div></div></div><div class=3D\"field field-name-field-datetim=\ne field-type-datetime field-label-inline clearfix\"><div class=3D\"field-labe=\nl\">When:&nbsp;</div><div class=3D\"field-items\"><div class=3D\"field-item eve=\nn\"><span class=3D\"date-display-single\">Monday, September 17, 2012 - Please check back later in 2012 for a definitive date.    The program=\n is free but reservations are necessary as capacity is limited.  Please cal=\nl 212-755-8532 x211 for reservations.</p>=0A</div></div></div><div class=3D=\n\"field field-name-field-datetime field-type-datetime field-label-inline cle=\narfix\"><div class=3D\"field-label\">When:&nbsp;</div><div class=3D\"field-item=\ns\"><div class=3D\"field-item even\"><span class=3D\"date-display-single\">Monda=\ny, November 12, 2012 - <span class=3D\"date-display-start\">6:00pm</span><spa=\nn class=3D\"date-display-separator\"> - </span><span class=3D\"date-display-en=\nd\">8:00pm</span></span></div></div></div><div class=3D\"field field-name-fie=\nld-venue field-type-text field-label-inline clearfix\"><div class=3D\"field-l=\nabel\">Venue:&nbsp;</div><div class=3D\"field-items\"><div class=3D\"field-item=\n even\">New York Genealogical and Biographical Society</div></div></div><div=\n class=3D\"field field-name-field-sponsor field-type-text field-label-inline=\n clearfix\"><div class=3D\"field-label\">Sponsor:&nbsp;</div><div class=3D\"fie=\nld-items\"><div class=3D\"field-item even\">Heraldry Committee of the NYG&B</d=\niv></div></div>  </div>=0A=0A  <ul class=3D\"links inline\"><li class=3D\"node=\n-readmore first last\"><a href=3D\"/heraldrywine\" rel=3D\"tag\" title=3D\"Herald=\nry on Wine Labels &amp; Ms. Bursey-Sabouri=\nn has been Fraser Herald at the Canadian Heraldic Authority in Ottawa since=\n 1989.  She is the principal artist of the Authority.  Bursey-Sabourin has =\nbeen responsible for the paintings made for the arms of the last five Gover=\nnors General of Canada and the Coat of arms of Canada.     The program is f=\nree but reservations are necessary as capacity is limited. Please call 212-=\n755-8532 x211 for reservations.</p>=0A</div></div></div><div class=3D\"field=\n field-name-field-datetime field-type-datetime field-label-inline clearfix\"=\n><div property=3D\"content:encoded\"><h2><img src=3D\"/sites/default/fil=\nes/images/1(3).png\" style=3D\"width: 170px; height: 250px; float: right;\" />=\nYou are invited to <a href=3D\"/worden-search\">Search Worden's Index</a>, wh=\nich contains over one million names that have appeared in <em>The Record</e=\nm> between 1870 and 2010.=C2=A0 Continuously published since 1870, the enti=\nre run of <em>The Record</em> comprises 567 issues at present and forms the=\n largest single collection of published material on families that lived in =\nNew York State.=C2=A0</h2>=0A<p>This comprehensive names index, originally =\ncreated by Mrs. Jean D. Worden and updated annually by NYG&amp;B volunteers=\n and interns, provides an invaluable research tool that has been appreciate=\nd by genealogical scholars everywhere. While anyone may search Worden's Ind=\nex, only NYG&amp;B members have online access to <em>The Record, </em>as we=\nll as specialized indexes and an Advanced Search function to help mine the =\nrich body of information contained in<em>The Record</em> collection.</p>=0A=\n<h3><a href=3D\"/nygbr\">Learn More</a> about <em>The Record.</em></h3>=0A<h3=\n><a href=3D\"/recordfundnonmbr\">Read</a> our <em>Guide to the Fundamentals o=\nf Using \"The Record\" Online.</em></h3>=0A<h3><a href=3D\"/join\">Join Now</a>=\n to enjoy access to <em>The Record </em>and our other online resources.</h3>=\n=0A<h4>=C2=A0</h4>=0A</div></div></div>  </div>=0A=0A  =0A  =0A</div>=0A  <=\n/div>=0A</div>=0A  </div>=0A      </article>=0A    </div>=0A    <footer>=0A=\n      <nav>=0A        <ul>=0A          <li><a href=3D\"/privacy\">Privacy</a>=\n</li>=0A          <li><a href=3D\"/service-terms\">Terms of Service</a></li>=\n=0A          <li><a href=3D\"/advertising\">Advertising</a></li>=0A          =\n<li><a href=3D\"/press\">Press Room</a></li>=0A          <li><a href=3D\"http:=\n//www.ironpaper.com\">Web Design</a></li>=0A        </ul>=0A        <a href=\n=3D\"http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-New-York-Genealogical-Biographical-So=\nciety/166498443372313\" rel=3D\"nofollow\"  target=3D\"_blank\"><img src=3D\"/sit=\nes/all/themes/nygbs/images/content-img/icon-facebook.png\" alt=3D\"Facebook p=\nage\"  border=3D\"0\" /></a>=0A            <a href=3D\"http://twitter.com/#!/ny=\nfamilyhistory\" rel=3D\"nofollow\" target=3D\"_blank\"><img src=3D\"/sites/all/th=\nemes/nygbs/images/content-img/icon-twitter.png\" alt=3D\"Twitter page\"  borde=\nr=3D\"0\" /></a>=0A            <a href=3D\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/nygbs/=\n\" rel=3D\"nofollow\"  target=3D\"_blank\"><img src=3D\"/sites/all/themes/nygbs/i=\nmages/content-img/icon-flickr.png\" alt=3D\"Flickr page\"  border=3D\"0\" /></a>=\n=0A      </nav>=0A     <div id=3D\"copyright\">=0A        New York Genealogic=\nal &amp;     =0A                =0A      </aside>=\n=0A            <article class=3D\"\">      =0A                =0A         <h1=\n class=3D\"title\" id=3D\"page-title\">=0A                      New York Geneal=\nogy: News You Can Use In Your New York Research           \t\t</h1>=0A       =\n=0A                  <div class=3D\"region region-content\">=0A    <div id=3D=\n\"block-system-main\" class=3D\"block block-system\">=0A=0A    =0A  <div class=\n=3D\"content\">=0A    <div id=3D\"node-460\" class=3D\"node node-page clearfix\" =\nabout=3D\"/newsyoucanuse\" typeof=3D\"foaf:Document\">=0A=0A  =0A      =0A  =0A=\n  <div class=3D\"content\">=0A    <span class=3D\"print-link\"><span class=3D\"p=\nrint_html\"><a href=3D\"http://newyorkfamilyhistory.org/print/460\" title=3D\"D=\nisplay a printer-friendly version of this page.\" class=3D\"print-page\" oncli=\nck=3D\"window.open(this.href); return false\" rel=3D\"nofollow\"><img class=3D\"=\nprint-icon print-icon-margin\" typeof=3D\"foaf:Image\" src=3D\"http://newyorkfa=\nmilyhistory.org/sites/all/modules/print/icons/print_icon.gif\" alt=3D\"Printe=\nr-friendly version\" title=3D\"Printer-friendly version\" />Printer-friendly v=\nersion</a></span></span><div class=3D\"field field-name-body field-type-text=\n-with-summary field-label-hidden\"><div class=3D\"field-items\"><div class=3D\"=\nfield-item even\" property=3D\"content:encoded\"><h2>This page gathers news it=\nems and tips that could benefit your New York research. Items are added fre=\nquently. If you have appropriate information to share, contact <a href=3D\"m=\nailto:webmaster@nygbs.org\">webmaster@nygbs.org</a>.</h2>=0A<div>=C2=A0</div>=\n=0A<h3>June 25, 2012: Black Gotham Online</h3>=0A<div>In 2011, Professor Ca=\nrla Peterson published a landmark book:<em> Black Gotham - A Family History=\n of African Americans in Nineteenth-Century New York</em> (Yale University =\nPress).=C2=A0 Recently, she launched a website/blog addressing much of the =\nsubject matter covered in the book. The new online material is at <a href=\n=3D\"http://www.blackgothamarchive.org\">www.blackgothamarchive.org</a>.=C2=\n=A0 This is a new resource for people researching this subject and time per=\niod.</div>=0A<h3>June 25, 2012: More New York data on FamilySearch.</h3>=0A=\n<div>Recently FamilySearch (<a href=3D\"http://www.familysearch.org\">www.fam=\nilysearch.org</a>) added additional browsable images for two existing datab=\nases: Orange County Probate Records and Queens County Probate Records.</div>=\n=0A<h3>June 6, 2012: New York State Censuses</h3>=0A<div>Ancestry.com has m=\nade available the New York state censuses for 1892, 1915 and 1925 online fo=\nr the first time, indexed by name.=C2=A0 If you are not an Ancestry.com sub=\nscriber and are a New York resident, these searchable databases are accessi=\nble for free. New York residents may sign in at this internet address: <a h=\nref=3D\"http://tinyurl.com/89cf6az\">http://tinyurl.com/89cf6az</a></div>=0A<=\nh3>June 6, 2012: 1940 Census for New York State is Now Searchable</h3>=0A<d=\niv>Ancestry.com has completed its index for New York State names in the 194=\n0 census and made it available to everyone for free.=C2=A0 However, the cen=\nsus pages themselves=C2=A0are available only to Ancestry.com subscribers an=\nd to patrons of libraries with Ancestry.com subscriptions. Some people have=\n commented on the high error rate. So search creatively (using wild cards, =\nfor example). And please post corrections. Each time you access a record, t=\nhere is an opportunity to post a correction, usually on the left side of th=\ne screen.</div>=0A<h3>June 5, 2012: War of 1812 Records</h3>=0A<div>Fold3.c=\nom, a subscription site, has made its War of 1812 records available for fre=\ne during June, 2012. Records include War of 1812 pension files; War of 1812=\n Prize Cases from the Southern District Court of New York, and War of 1812 =\nService Records.</div>=0A<div>=C2=A0</div>=0A<h3>June 4, 2012: 1940 New Yor=\nk Census Indexing</h3>=0A<div>Some New York localities, including a portion=\n of the Bronx, have been indexed and are searchable online at <a href=3D\"ht=\ntp://www.myheritage.com/\">www.myheritage.com</a>.=C2=A0 This information is=\n free.</div>=0A<h3>May 16, 2012: Two Exhibitions</h3>=0A<div>Two exhibition=\ns of interest have recently opened. The <a href=3D\"http://www.rchsonline.or=\ng/\" target=3D\"_blank\">Rensselaer County Historical Society</a> has a new ex=\nhibition on the Great Fire of Troy, New York (1862); the <a href=3D\"http://=\nlibrary.nysha.org/entry_list.asp\" target=3D\"_blank\">New York State Historic=\nal Association Research Library</a> in Cooperstown has a new exhibition on =\nthe photographs of Cooperstown (1965-1992) made by Milo Stewart.</div>=0A<h=\n3>May 14, 2012: New York Newspapers Online</h3>=0A<div><a href=3D\"http://ww=\nw.genealogybank.com/\" target=3D\"_blank\">Genealogybank.com</a>, a subscripti=\non website, has added more New Jersey and New York material to its vast new=\nspaper archive. (The database is searchable by non-subscribers but the full=\n articles cannot be accessed without a subscription.) The following communi=\nties and newspaper titles are affected by this announcement:</div>=0A<div>=\n=C2=A0</div>=0A<div>Newark, NJ: New Jersey Deutsche Zeitung<br />Trenton, N=\nJ: Sentinel <br />Trenton, NJ: Trenton Evening Times<br />Albany, NY: Alban=\ny Argus =C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 <br />Auburn, NY: Auburn Journal and Advertiser<=\nbr />Auburn, NY: Cayuga Republican <br />New York City: Commercial Advertis=\ner<br />New York City: Evening Post<br />New York City: New York Age<br />N=\new York City: New York Freeman<br />Schenectady, NY: Cabinet<br />Utica, NY=\n: Columbian Gazette</div>=0A<div>=C2=A0</div>=0A<h3>April 25, 2012: Large N=\nYC Photo Archive Officially Online</h3>=0A<p>The NYC Department of records =\nannounced that 870,000 photographs are officially added to the <a href=3D\"h=\nttp://www.nyc.gov/html/records/html/misc/luna.shtml\" target=3D\"_blank\">Muni=\ncipal Archives Online Gallery</a>. This was previously noted here on March =\n26. Heavy traffic has temporarily disabled the site but they are inviting p=\natrons to check back at a later date.</p>=0A<h3>April 20, 2012: News For Th=\nose Researching Eastern European Jewish Families</h3>=0A<div>The Center for=\n Jewish History in Manhattan (<a href=3D\"http://www.cjh.org/\" target=3D\"_bl=\nank\">cjh.org</a>) has announced a partnership with the Miriam Weiner Routes=\n to Roots Foundation to make archives and images from Eastern Europe availa=\nble online. The details are on the Center for Jewish History website.</div>=\n=0A<h3>April 11, 2012: New Data on FamilySearch for New York and New Jersey=\n</h3>=0A<div><a href=3D\"https://www.familysearch.org/\" target=3D\"_blank\">Fa=\nmilySearch</a> has announced new data: 1) New York Naturalizations (1792-19=\n76) from eleven upstate counties plus New York County and Queens County. Th=\ne collection contains 951,000 browsable images searchable by county. 2) New=\n Jersey Marriages (1682-1956). This collection contains about 60,000 search=\nable images and is complete.</div>=0A<div>=C2=A0</div>=0A<h3>April 3, 2012:=\n New York Data free on Ancestry.com if you are a New Yorker</h3>=0A<p>The N=\new York Archives Partnership Trust has reminded researchers that New York S=\ntate databases are online at Ancestry.com and are accessible for free by Ne=\nw Yorkers. If you are a New Yorker but NOT an Ancestry.com subscriber, you =\ncan get a special account to search these New York State records.<br />The =\ndata can be accessed through the New York State Archives webpage <a href=3D=\n\"http://www.archives.nysed.gov/\" target=3D\"_blank\">www.archives.nysed.gov</=\na>.=C2=A0 From this page, click on \"research\" and then you will see the lin=\nk to Ancestry.com.<br /><br />(By the way, The New York Archives Partnershi=\np Trust is a member supported organization that is very much worth explorin=\ng if you have not already done so. This organization does exceptional work =\nand offers sophisticated public programs, many of which are genealogically =\nrelevant.)<br /><br />New York State data in the Ancestry.com New York sect=\nion includes this list which we have copied from the Ancestry.com New York =\npage. <br />Albany, New York State Census, 1915<br />New York Marriages, 16=\n00-1784<br />New York Military Equipment Claims, War of 1812<br />New York,=\n Census of Inmates in Almshouses and Poorhouses, 1830-1920<br />New York, C=\nivil War Muster Roll Abstracts, 1861-1900<br />New York, Town Clerks' Regis=\nters of Men Who Served in the Civil War, ca 1861-1865<br />New York, World =\nWar I Veterans' Service Data, 1913-1919<br />Salina, New York, Records, 180=\n5-1969<br />U.S. Census Mortality Schedules, New York, 1850-1880<br />U.S. =\nCensus Non-Population Schedules, New York, 1850-1880<br />U.S. Federal Cens=\nus - 1880 Schedules of Defective, Dependent, and Delinquent Classes</p>=0A<=\ndiv>=C2=A0</div>=0A<h3>April 2, 2012: A Handy 1940 Census Application if yo=\nu are searching in New York City.</h3>=0A<div>Today is the long-awaited rel=\nease date for the 1940 census. If you are searching for people living in Ne=\nw York City in 1940, and need to identify their enumeration districts, the =\nNew York Public Library has an effective <a href=3D\"http://directme.nypl.or=\ng/\" target=3D\"_blank\">online search tool</a> developed by the NYPL's brainy=\n and creative digital labs group.=C2=A0</div>=0A<div>=C2=A0</div>=0A<div>Yo=\nu begin by searching for your people in the online 1940s phone directory fo=\nr New York City.=C2=A0 At the moment, the directory is accessible from the =\nhomepage of the NYPL's site at <a href=3D\"http://www.nypl.org/\" target=3D\"_=\nblank\">www.nypl.org</a>.=C2=A0 The application then instantly maps your peo=\nple's locations and uses the map information combined with the Stephen Mors=\ne One-Step tool to identify the relevant enumeration districts. Once you ha=\nve the enumeration districts, you can go to the <a href=3D\"http://1940censu=\ns.archives.gov/\" target=3D\"_blank\">NARA website</a> (or another site postin=\ng the digital images of the 1940 census) and find your people.</div>=0A<div=\n>=C2=A0</div>=0A<div>The NYPL application also gives you an opportunity to =\npost information about your people on the NYPL website which will be tagged=\n to the name and the map location. Potentially this could add enormous valu=\ne to the 1940 phone book and the 1940 census tracking that will take place =\non the NYPL's website.</div>=0A<div>=C2=A0</div>=0A<div>You might also look=\n at the other projects that the digital labs group is working on at the NYP=\nL. They are not all genealogically related, but they all demonstrate the ki=\nnd of advanced digital work that the NYPL is spearheading.</div>=0A<div>=C2=\n=A0</div>=0A<h3>April 1, 2012: World War I Registration Forms</h3>=0A<div>F=\namilySearch has recently added 25 million World War I registration forms to=\n its website. Many originate in New York State. The browsable images are ar=\nranged by state, and then by counties and cities. For counties and smaller =\ncities, browsing the alphabetized forms will not be a problem. For larger c=\nities, especially New York City, searching will be more tedious because ima=\nges are arranged by draft board number.</div>=0A<h3>March 26, 2012: Digital=\n Photos online at the New York City Municipal Archives</h3>=0A<p class=3D\"M=\nsoNoSpacing\">The New York City Municipal Archives has recently placed onlin=\ne almost 872,000 digital photographs from several collections. <a href=3D\"h=\nttp://mtprawvwdorlna1.nyc.gov/luna/servlet\">http://mtprawvwdorlna1.nyc.gov/=\nluna/servlet</a>.=C2=A0 Part of the online offering is the 1980s tax photog=\nraphs collection that includes a photo of every building in New York City. =\nOther collections are Maps and Atlases; Public Charities and Hospitals; and=\n the WPA Federal Writers Project. The Municipal Archives website catalogs t=\nhe full offering.</p>=0A<h3>March 20, 2012: Finding Your Roots with Henry L=\nouis Gates, Jr.</h3>=0A<p>Henry Louis Gates, Jr.'s new series \"Finding Your=\n Roots\" begins this Sunday, March 25th, at 8pm on your local PBS station. T=\nhe first episode features Harry Connick, Jr. and Branford Marsalis. The sec=\nond features Cory Booker, mayor of Newark, New Jersey, and Congressman John=\n Lewis of Georgia. We have seen the second episode, and it is inspiring and=\n powerful.=C2=A0 The producers shot scenes from three episodes in the serie=\ns in our offices on West 44th Street. Professor Gates is a trustee of the N=\nYG&amp;B.</p>=0A<h3>March 10, 2012: New York newspapers now online</h3>=0A<=\np><a href=3D\"http://www.genealogybank.com/\" target=3D\"_blank\">Genealogybank=\n.com</a>, a subscription site, has announced the addition of new newspaper =\ndata. Included are papers from New York: Albany, Canandaigua, Geneva, Glen =\nCove, New York City, Plattsburgh, Schenectady, and Waterford. Checking the =\ntitles and dates does not require a subscription.</p>=0A<h3>March 9, 2012: =\nNew New York Probate Records online.</h3>=0A<p><a href=3D\"https://www.famil=\nysearch.org/\" target=3D\"_blank\">FamilySearch</a> announced a significant ad=\ndition of new data, including more probate records from Orange (1787-1938) =\nand Queens (1899-1921) Counties, New York. The collection includes browsabl=\ne images which are not yet indexed.</p>=0A<h3>February 27, 2012: Civil War =\nservice records on Fold3.com</h3>=0A<p><a href=3D\"http://www.fold3.com/\">Fo=\nld3</a> (formerly Footnote) has started adding compiled service records for=\n Union troops from New York, Massachusetts, Ohio, and Pennsylvania. Fold3 r=\nequires a subscription to access; some libraries, including the New York Pu=\nblic Library, have subscriptions.</p>=0A<h3>February 16, 2012: New Newspape=\nrs at Genealogybank.com</h3>=0A<p>Recently, <a href=3D\"http://www.genealogy=\nbank.com/\">Genealogybank.com</a> announced additions to its newspaper archi=\nve. These include supplementary material from Cazenovia, New York City, Sar=\natoga Springs, and Albany papers. A new title was added: <em>Auburn Journal=\n and Advertiser</em> (1837-1846). A blog beginning in 2011 was added for Sy=\nracuse. <a href=3D\"http://www.genealogybank.com/\">Genealogybank.com</a> is =\na subscription site.</p>=0A<h3>February 3, 2012: Fold3 Makes Nearly 3 Milli=\non African American Records Free During Black History Month</h3>=0A<p><a hr=\nef=3D\"http://www.fold3.com/\">Fold3</a> is giving free access to their Black=\n History Collection in honor of Black History Month. This collection includ=\nes historical records documenting African American achievements and will be=\n available the entire month of February. <a href=3D\"http://www.genealogyblo=\ng.com/?p=3D16832\" target=3D\"_blank\">Click here for more information</a>. <b=\nr /><br /></p>=0A<h3>January 20, 2012: New Revolutionary War Records Online=\n</h3>=0A<p><a href=3D\"http://www.fold3.com/\">Fold3</a>, a fee-based subscri=\nption website that is owned by <a href=3D\"http://www.ancestry.com/\">Ancestr=\ny.com</a>, recently announced the addition of \"numbered record books.\" Thes=\ne documents concern Revolutionary War military operations and service, pay =\nand settlement of accounts, and supplies, and were digitized from microfilm=\n at NARA. There is extensive New York material in this database. The introd=\nuctory material on the Fold3 website includes a very detailed finding aid p=\nrepared by NARA.</p>=0A<h3>January 11, 2012: FamilySearch Datebase Update</=\nh3>=0A<p><a href=3D\"http://newyorkfamilyhistory.org/node/460/FamilySearch.o=\nrg\" target=3D\"_blank\">FamilySearch.org</a> reports additions to the New Yor=\nk State Census (1875), New York probate records (various locations), and Qu=\neens County probate records.</p>=0A<h3>January 11, 2012: Maps at the New Yo=\nrk Public Library</h3>=0A<p>A blog post by by the New York Public Library's=\n Matt Knutzen describes techniques for using digital maps. He reports that =\nthe NYPL has now scanned nearly all public domain New York City atlases, a =\ncollection of over 10,000 maps.=C2=A0 Read the post to learn more about how=\n these maps can be used in your genealogical research.=C2=A0 <br /><a href=\n=3D\"http://www.nypl.org/blog/2012/01/10/unbinding-atlas-working-digital-map=\ns\" target=3D\"_blank\">http://www.nypl.org/blog/2012/01/10/unbinding-atlas-wo=\nrking-digital-maps</a></p>=0A<h3>January 10, 2012: New York Maps Online</h3>=\n=0A<p><a href=3D\"http://www.historygeo.com/\" target=3D\"_blank\">HistoryGeo.c=\nom</a> is a new, subscription-based website offering a library of maps. The=\n New York \"map-projects\" on the site are 1) Atlas of Delaware County (F.W. =\nBeers, 1869); 2) Sweets New Atlas of Onondaga County (1874); and 3) Otsego =\nCounty (1903).=C2=A0 Within each=C2=A0of these=C2=A0map-projects are many t=\nown maps.</p>=0A<h3>January 9, 2012: New NY Newspapers Online</h3>=0A<p><a =\nhref=3D\"http://www.genealogybank.com/\" target=3D\"_blank\">Genealogybank.com<=\n/a>, a subscription site, recently announced new additions to their New Yor=\nk newspaper archive online. All of these new additions are from New York <e=\nm>City</em> papers.=C2=A0</p>=0A<p>Daily People (1901-1906)<br />Irish Amer=\nican Weekly (1873-1914)<br />Irish Nation (1881-1883) NEW TITLE<br />People=\n (1891-1896)<br />Socialist Call (1944-1948)<br />Truth (1880-1884)<br />Wo=\nrker (1903-1907)</p>=0A<h3>January 6, 2012: Save the Date: Sunday, March 25=\n, 2012</h3>=0A<p>\"Finding Your Roots\" with NYG&amp;B trustee Henry Louis Ga=\ntes, Jr., a new 10-part PBS series, begins on Sunday, March 25. Featured su=\nbjects include Harry Connick, Jr.; Robert Downey, Jr.; Samuel L. Jackson; B=\narbara Walters; Newark, N.J. Mayor Cory Booker; and Kevin Bacon and Kyra Se=\ngwick, among others. The NYG&amp;B helped with the research on the Bacon/Se=\ndwick episode, and a large part of the Samuel L. Jackson episode was taped =\nin the NYG&amp;B's office on West 44th Street. The series runs through May.=\n =C2=A0<a href=3D\"http://www.wnet.org/pressroom/release.php?get=3D3839\" tar=\nget=3D\"_blank\">Click here</a>=C2=A0for more information.=C2=A0</p>=0A<h3>De=\ncember 27, 2011: eBooks from the New York Public Library</h3>=0A<p>The New =\nYork Public Library website is now offering instruction on downloading eboo=\nks to Kindle, Nook, and other devices from their collection online at <a hr=\nef=3D\"http://www.nypl.org/ask-nypl/ebookcentral\" target=3D\"_blank\">http://w=\nww.nypl.org/ask-nypl/ebookcentral</a>. The NYPL offers many thousands of fr=\nee ebooks from all fields of inquiry, in addition to the usual bestsellers.=\n</p>=0A<h3>December 27, 2011: More additions to New York databases on Famil=\nySearch.org</h3>=0A<p><a href=3D\"http://newyorkfamilyhistory.org/node/460/F=\namilySearch.org\" target=3D\"_blank\">FamilySearch.org</a> continues to update=\n Orange County Probate Records (1787-1938) and has updated New York Marriag=\nes (1908-1935); this database offers images but is not searchable. The marr=\niage database updates cover 45 counties in New York State; New York City co=\nunties are not in this group. The marriage database is searchable, with ima=\nges.</p>=0A<h3>December 12, 2011: New-York Historical Society Library News<=\n/h3>=0A<p>The New-York Historical Society has new library policies research=\ners should know about. Registration and a government-issued photo ID are no=\nw required to use the library, and casual visits simply to browse the shelv=\nes are not permitted. Visit their magnificant new website (<a href=3D\"http:=\n//www.nyhistory.org/\">nyhistory.org</a>) to register in advance.=C2=A0 Curr=\nently, hours are Tuesday-Friday from 9am to 3pm, and Saturdays from 10am to=\n 1pm. The library is closed on Sundays and Mondays.</p>=0A<h3>December 12, =\n2011: Additions to New York databases on FamilySearch.org</h3>=0A<p>Two exi=\nsting databases on FamilySearch.org have additions of new images: Orange an=\nd Queens County Probate Records. The images are browsable but not searchabl=\ne.</p>=0A<h3>December 8, 2011: Lefferts Family Documents at new Brooklyn Hi=\nstorical Society Website</h3>=0A<p>The Brooklyn Historical Society has just=\n launched a new website entitled <a href=3D\"http://www.brooklynhistory.org/=\nexhibitions/lefferts/resources/\" target=3D\"_blank\">\"An American Family Grow=\ns in Brooklyn: The Lefferts Family Papers at the Brooklyn Historical Societ=\ny.\"</a> The website includes an image gallery and information about related=\n collections there. These collections include Brevoort Family (1760-1879), =\nLott Family(1702-1954), Charles A. Ditmas (1687-1935), DeWitt Clinton, Gert=\nrude Lefferts Vanderbilt (1737-1818), Gabriel Furman, Nehemiah Denton (1785=\n-1844), and the Brooklyn Civil War Relief Association, among others. The Le=\nfferts family, a Dutch family, was important in the development of Kings Co=\nunty.</p>=0A<h3>December 5, 2011: New data on FamilySearch</h3>=0A<p>Recent=\n announcement of new data online at FamilySearch.org included New Jersey co=\nunty marriage records (1682-1956), both browsable and searchable. Large amo=\nunts of data from other states and countries was also included.</p>=0A<h3>N=\november 18, 2011: New website launching about New Amsterdam</h3>=0A<p>The N=\new Amsterdam History Center will launch a preview version of its new websit=\ne: <a href=3D\"http://www.newamsterdamhistorycenter.org/\" target=3D\"_blank\">=\nwww.newamsterdamhistorycenter.org</a> on Saturday, November 19 (tomorrow).=\n=C2=A0 The preview version includes some useful links, a sample of useful i=\nnformation, and a virtual 3-D \"tour\" of New Amsterdam. Persons interested i=\nn this topic will want to bookmark the site and check it from time to time =\nas it expands.</p>=0A<h3>November 11, 2011: Tips for locating obituaries fr=\nom the New York Public Library's Milstein Division</h3>=0A<p>Recently, Carm=\nen Nigro, from the Milstein Division at the New York Public Library, posted=\n a helpful article on finding obituaries. The posting is not a database of =\nobituaries but rather some very useful information about locating them. To =\nread this article go to: =C2=A0<a href=3D\"http://nypl.org/blog/2011/11/09/g=\nreat-obituary-hunt-genealogy-research-guide\">nypl.org/blog/2011/11/09/great=\n-obituary-hunt-genealogy-research-guide</a></p>=0A<h3>November 8, 2011: Cat=\nalogs of Knoedler &amp; Co. (1869-1946)</h3>=0A<p>The website of the Metrop=\nolitan Museum of Art now has a searchable collection of exhibition catalogs=\n of Knoedler &amp; Company, the important New York art gallery. The collect=\nion contains nearly 900 catalogs and unpublished materials created between =\n1869 and 1946. Lists of collectors and lendors might be of interest as well=\n as rare images of places, people, and historical subjects. The digital col=\nlections of the Watson Library at the Metropolitan Museum are at <a href=3D=\n\"http://libmma.org/\">libmma.org</a>=C2=A0 These materials are also availabl=\ne online at Arcade (<a href=3D\"http://www.arcade.nyarc.org/\">arcade.nyarc.o=\nrg</a>) and WorldCat.</p>=0A<h3>November 7, 2011: Expansive New New York St=\nate Data on Ancestry.com</h3>=0A<p>The New York State Archives website just=\n announced a link to special New York State data on <a href=3D\"http://newyo=\nrkfamilyhistory.org/node/460/Ancestry.com\" target=3D\"_blank\">Ancestry.com</=\na>. The New York State Archives requires that data from state government co=\nllections be free for New York State residents even if posted to a subscrip=\ntion site or a non-governmental site.=C2=A0 Ancestry.com subscribers also h=\nave access to these databases. For details visit <a href=3D\"http://www.arch=\nives.nysed.gov/\">www.archives.nysed.gov</a>. The current databases on Ances=\ntry.com that are part of this agreement are:</p>=0A<ul><li>Albany, New York=\n State Census, 1915</li>=0A<li>New York Marriages, 1600-1784</li>=0A<li>New=\n York Military Equipment Claims, War of 1812</li>=0A<li>New York, Census of=\n Inmates in Almshouses and Poorhouses, 1830-1920 Updated</li>=0A<li>New Yor=\nk, Civil War Muster Roll Abstracts, 1861-1900</li>=0A<li>New York, Town Cle=\nrks' Registers of Men Who Served in the Civil War, ca 1861-1865</li>=0A<li>=\nSalina (Onondaga County), New York, Records, 1805-1969</li>=0A<li>U.S. Cens=\nus Mortality Schedules, New York, 1850-1880</li>=0A<li>U.S. Census Non-Popu=\nlation Schedules, New York, 1850-1880</li>=0A<li>U.S. Federal Census - 1880=\n Schedules of Defective, Dependent, and Delinquent Classes</li>=0A</ul><h3>=\nNovember 2, 2011: New-York Historical Society Reopening on Nov. 11.</h3>=0A=\n<p>Welcome back!=C2=A0 The New-York Historical Society reopens on 11/11/11.=\n=C2=A0 After that date, the research library will be open on its regular ho=\nurs (after a period of construction during which it was open by appointment=\n). Their new website has been up for several weeks, and we think it's spect=\nacular. Visit the website (<a href=3D\"http://www.nyhistory.org\">www.nyhisto=\nry.org</a>) for information on programs that provide historical context for=\n New York family history researchers and for information about accessing th=\ne astounding resources in the research library. =C2=A0</p>=0A<h3>October 31=\n, 2011: Ancestry.com Database Additions</h3>=0A<p>Recently Ancestry.com ann=\nounced postings of 53 new databases containing 120 million new names. There=\n were no New York databases in the roster, but there were items from New Je=\nrsey (births and christenings; deaths and burials) and Connecticut (deaths =\nand burials.) However, see note above dated Nov. 7, 2011 reporting new New =\nYork data on Ancestry.com.</p>=0A<h3>October 17, 2011: \"The History of Broo=\nklyn Jewry\" online</h3>=0A<p>\"Nu? What's New,\" the weekly e-News of Avotayn=\nu, Inc. reports that <em>The </em><span style=3D\"font-style: italic;\">Histo=\nry of Brooklyn Jewry</span> by Samuel F. Abelow (Scheba Publishing Company,=\n Brooklyn, NY, 1937) has been added to Google Books. See the title online a=\nt=C2=A0 <a href=3D\"http://tinyurl.com/3vy36xb\" target=3D\"_blank\">http://tin=\nyurl.com/3vy36xb</a>.=C2=A0 The book's index is not adequate to search the =\ncontents, so the online search function will make the book much more access=\nible.</p>=0A<h3>October 14, 2011: New NYPL Catalog</h3>=0A<p>The New York P=\nublic Library has unveiled a new catalog with a number of new features. Amo=\nng them is an improved ability to limit searches, making your catalog searc=\nh more efficient. To see the new catalog, go to the homepage of the NYPL we=\nbsite (<a href=3D\"http://www.nypl.org/\" target=3D\"_blank\">www.nypl.org</a>)=\n, and click on the Research tab. Then click on \"Classic Catalog.\" When you =\nare on that catalog page, click on \"Catalog FAQs\" to learn more. Or experim=\nent with a catalog search.</p>=0A<h3>October 11, 2011: New Kinship website<=\n/h3>=0A<h3>=0A<!--[if gte mso 10]> <mce:style><!   /* Style Definitions */ =\n table.MsoNormalTable \t{mso-style-name:\"Table Normal\"; \tmso-tstyle-rowband-=\nsize:0; \tmso-tstyle-colband-size:0; \tmso-style-noshow:yes; \tmso-style-prior=\nity:99; \tmso-style-qformat:yes; \tmso-style-parent:\"\"; \tmso-padding-alt:0in =\n5.4pt 0in 5.4pt; \tmso-para-margin:0in; \tmso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt; \tms=\no-pagination:widow-orphan; \tfont-size:11.0pt; \tfont-family:\"Calibri\",\"sans-=\nserif\"; \tmso-ascii-font-family:Calibri; \tmso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin; =\n\tmso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\"; \tmso-fareast-theme-font:minor-f=\nareast; \tmso-hansi-font-family:Calibri; \tmso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;}=\n  > <! class=3D\"field-item even\" property=3D\"content:encoded\"><p>Harry =\nMacy, Jr., FASG, FGBS, who was Editor of <em>The NYG&amp;B Record</em> from=\n 1987 through 2006, compiled this index as a continuation of Mrs. Jean D. <=\nem>Worden=E2=80=99s Master Index 1870-1982</em>. It consists of three parts=\n: compiled genealogies and family records, indexed by principal surnames; s=\nource records and collective genealogies, indexed by location; and other ar=\nticles, indexed by subject.=C2=A0 The abbreviation A/C refers to Additions =\nand Corrections to prior articles, published in each October issue.</p>=0A<=\ndiv><br />Click here to browse or search the <strong><a Biographical Record 1983-2011 (Volumes 114-142)</em></a></strong>.</=\ndiv>=0A</div></div></div>  </div>=0A=0A  =0A  =0A</div>=0A  </div>=0A</div>=\n=0A  </div>=0A      </article>=0A    </div>=0A class=\n=3D\"element-invisible\">Secondary menu</h2><ul id=3D\"secondary-menu-links\" c=\nlass=3D\"links clearfix\"><li class=3D\"menu-1187 first\"><a href=3D\"/about-nyg=\nb\" title=3D\"\">About the </aside>=0A            =\n<article class=3D\"\">      =0A                =0A         <h1 class=3D\"title=\n\" id=3D\"page-title\">=0A                      Frequently Asked Questions abo=\nut the NYG&amp;B            \t\t</h1>=0A       =0A                  <div clas=\ns=3D\"region region-content\">=0A    <div id=3D\"block-system-main\" class=3D\"b=\nlock block-system\">=0A=0A    =0A  <div class=3D\"content\">=0A    <div id=3D\"=\nnode-31\" class=3D\"node node-page clearfix\" about=3D\"/nygbs-faq\" typeof=3D\"f=\noaf:Document\">=0A=0A  =0A      =0A  =0A  <div class=3D\"content\">=0A    <spa=\nn class=3D\"print-link\"><span class=3D\"print_html\"><a href=3D\"http://newyork=\nfamilyhistory.org/print/31\" title=3D\"Display a printer-friendly version of =\nthis page.\" class=3D\"print-page\" onclick=3D\"window.open(this.href); return =\nfalse\" rel=3D\"nofollow\"><img class=3D\"print-icon print-icon-margin\" typeof=\n=3D\"foaf:Image\" src=3D\"http://newyorkfamilyhistory.org/sites/all/modules/pr=\nint/icons/print_icon.gif\" alt=3D\"Printer-friendly version\" title=3D\"Printer=\n-friendly version\" />Printer-friendly version</a></span></span><div class=\n=3D\"field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden\">=\n<div class=3D\"field-items\"><div class=3D\"field-item even\" property=3D\"conte=\nnt:encoded\"><div>=0A<h2><a name=3D\"top\" id=3D\"top\"></a>Here are frequently =\nasked questions and answers. If you need further help, <a href=3D\"/contact-=\nus\" target=3D\"_self\">contact us</a> via email or phone.=C2=A0</h2>=0A<h2>Go=\n directly to <a href=3D\"#Website Questions\">questions about our website</a>=\n.</h2>=0A<p> <br /><br /></p><h3>Can I visit the NYG&amp;B?</h3>=0A<p>Membe=\nrs are welcome to visit the NYG&amp;B by appointment. Since we gave our res=\nearch collections to the NYPL in 2008, we do not have a research library in=\n our facility. We encourage you to do research at the New York Public Libra=\nry, located a few short blocks from our offices. Also, while you are in the=\n New York City area, plan to visit the other research centers in New York C=\nity (including the Municipal Archives, the National Archives in New York Ci=\nty, and the New-York Historical Society) and other locations.</p>=0A<h3>Wha=\nt is the NYG&amp;B=E2=80=99s relationship with the New York Public Library =\n(NYPL)?</h3>=0A<p>The NYG&amp;B and the NYPL are complementary though entir=\nely independent organizations.</p>=0A<p>In 2008, the NYG&amp;B gave its col=\nlection of books and research material to the NYPL along with support to ad=\nd it to the <a href=3D\"http://www.nypl.org/collections\" target=3D\"_blank\">N=\nYPL=E2=80=99s digital catalog</a>.=C2=A0 For assistance to find items from =\nthe NYG&amp;B Collection at the NYPL and for Catalog search tips, read our =\n<a href=3D\"/nyplsearch\">guide</a>.</p>=0A<p>An extraordinarily large propor=\ntion of researchers at the NYPL are working on family history research, and=\n the various departments of the NYPL constitute one of the great genealogic=\nal research resources in the world. The Milstein Division of the NYPL is th=\ne centerpiece of that resource. View our <a href=3D\"/librarycollection\">gui=\nde to the resources of the NYPL for genealogists</a>.</p>=0A<p>The NYG&amp;=\nB and the NYPL jointly sponsor educational programs that take place in the =\nStephen Schwarzman Building on 42<sup>nd</sup> Street in New York City. The=\n NYG&amp;B also produces programming of its own that is offered there and e=\nlsewhere.=C2=A0 The NYG&amp;B participates with the NYPL=E2=80=99s educatio=\nn department to produce programming for students, teachers, and patrons of =\nthe NYPL=E2=80=99s branch libraries.</p>=0A<h3>I want to find out about my =\nfamily but I don=E2=80=99t know where to start. Could the NYG&amp;B help me=\n get started?</h3>=0A<p>We encourage you to start by reading our guide for =\nbeginners, <a href=3D\"/member-gettingstarted\">Getting Started On Your Famil=\ny History</a>, which will give you the best methods to start your search. P=\nlan to join us at some of our <a href=3D\"/nygbs-events\">events,</a> where y=\nou=E2=80=99ll hear expert advice and guidance for your search.</p>=0A<h3>Do=\n you have a list of genealogists for hire?</h3>=0A<p>Yes. We have compiled =\n<a href=3D\"/professional-genealogists\">a list of genealogists</a> available=\n to help you. You may also=C2=A0 visit the website of the <a href=3D\"http:/=\n/www.apgen.org\" target=3D\"_blank\">Association of Professional Genealogists<=\n/a> where you will find a list of members and their specialties. Note that =\nmembership in the APG is not itself a credential.</p>=0A<h3>I posted a quer=\ny in the Genealogical Exchange and it didn't show up. Why?</h3>=0A<p>Querie=\ns first need to be approved by an administrator. That means there is a wait=\n time for the posting of queries. We try to review queries once every busin=\ness day.</p>=0A<h3>How can I participate with the NYG&amp;B?</h3>=0A<p>The =\nbest way to participate is by volunteering. There are all kinds of tasks th=\nat need support, some of which can be done from home. See the next question=\n below.</p>=0A<p>Read a <a href=3D\"/volunteer-opportunties\">description of =\ncurrent volunteer opportunities</a>, along with the qualifications and time=\n commitment for each position. Some assignments require your presence on-si=\nte at the NYG&amp;B during business hours while others can be accomplished =\nin your own home on your own schedule.</p>=0A<h3>What does it cost to becom=\ne a member of the NYG&amp;B?</h3>=0A<p>We offer memberships in the online s=\ntore. The basic annual membership for an individual is $60. The best value =\nmembership is the two-year membership at $100.</p>=0A<h3>How can I sign up =\nfor an event?</h3>=0A<p>You=E2=80=99re welcome to <a href=3D\"https://newyor=\nkfamilyhistory.myshopify.com/collections/events\" target=3D\"_self\">sign up</=\na> for an event through our website or by calling our Education Department =\nat <span class=3D\"skype_pnh_print_container\">212-755-8532</span><span class=\n=3D\"skype_pnh_container\"><span class=3D\"skype_pnh_mark\">, </span></span>ext=\n. 211.=C2=A0 Generally events that require a payment for admission have lim=\nited seating, and so advance purchase is necessary. Many events are free an=\nd do not require advance sign-up.</p>=0A<h3>The event that I want is sold o=\nut. What should I do?</h3>=0A<p>You may call our Education Department <span=\n class=3D\"skype_pnh_container\"><span class=3D\"skype_pnh_highlighting_inacti=\nve_common\"><span class=3D\"skype_pnh_textarea_span\"><span class=3D\"skype_pnh=\n_text_span\">at 212-755-8532</span></span><span class=3D\"skype_pnh_right_spa=\nn\">, </span></span></span>ext. 211 to be placed on a wait-list for the even=\nt.=C2=A0</p>=0A<h3>Are your events free?</h3>=0A<p>It depends on the event =\nand the location. Information on pricing for each event is available in the=\n event description. =C2=A0When there is a charge for NYG&amp;B events, memb=\ners receive a substantial discount.</p>=0A<h3><a name=3D\"Website Questions\"=\n id=3D\"Website Questions\">I need to report an error on your website. </a></=\nh3>=0A<p>Please email <a href=3D\"mailto:systems@nygbs.org\">webmaster@nygbs.=\norg</a> with any errors or omissions that you see on our website.</p>=0A<h3=\n>I=E2=80=99ve forgotten my username and password =E2=80=93 what should I do=\n?</h3>=0A<p>First click the login button. At the next screen, click \"forgot=\n your user name and password\" and follow the instructions.=C2=A0 A link wil=\nl be sent to your email account that allows you to reset your password.=C2=\n=A0 If the link does not work or you do not receive an email, please call u=\ns at 212-755-8532 during regular business hours, or send email to <a href=\n=3D\"mailto:administration@nygbs.org\">webmaster@nygbs.org</a>. We will respo=\nnd promptly.=C2=A0</p>=0A<h3>I know my username and password, but they don'=\nt work =E2=80=93 what should I do?</h3>=0A<p>First click the login button. =\nAt the next screen, click \"forgot your user name and password\" and follow t=\nhe instructions.=C2=A0 A link will be sent to your email account that allow=\ns you to reset your password.=C2=A0 If the link does not work or you do not=\n receive an email, please call us at 212-755-8532 during regular business h=\nours, or send email to <a href=3D\"mailto:administration@nygbs.org\">webmaste=\nr@nygbs.org</a>. We will respond promptly.</p>=0A<h3>I'm a member and I wan=\nt to use the website but I've never been given a username and password =E2=\n=80=93 what should I do?</h3>=0A<p>Please send an email to <a href=3D\"mailt=\no:administration@nygbs.org\">webmaster@nygbs.org</a> or call us at 212-755-8=\n532 during regular business hours and we will set you up with a username an=\nd password.=C2=A0</p>=0A<h3>How do I search the NYG&amp;B=E2=80=99s website=\n?</h3>=0A<p>The NYG&amp;B=E2=80=99s new website allows you to do a global s=\nearch <em>of the website</em> using the search bar at the top right of your=\n screen.=C2=A0 This website search does not apply to the contents of our eL=\nibrary, which may searched separately.=C2=A0 Follow this <a href=3D\"/elibus=\nergood\">User's Guide</a> to learn how to optimize your experience of the eL=\nibrary, including the best way to search the eLibrary collections.</p>=0A<h=\n3>What is the best way to search the eLibrary?</h3>=0A<p>Follow this <a hre=\nf=3D\"/elibusergood\">User's Guide</a> to learn how to optimize your experien=\nce of the eLibrary, including the best way to search the eLibrary collectio=\nns.</p>=0A<h3>What is the most effective way to search <em>The Record</em> =\nonline?</h3>=0A<p>Read our <a href=3D\"/recordfundnonmbr\"><span style=3D\"tex=\nt-decoration: underline;\">detailed instructions</span></a></p>=0A<h3>How ca=\nn I print pages from the eLibrary?</h3>=0A<p>Press CTRL+P or right click on=\n your mouse and choose print. You will be given the option to print the who=\nle document or singular pages.</p>=0A<h3>What new materials have you added =\nto the website?</h3>=0A<p>View a list of new and updated <a href=3D\"/public=\n-researchtool\">Research Tools</a>; view a list of our expanded <a href=3D\"/=\npublic-elibrary\">eLibrary</a> and click on a title for further information.=\n</p>=0A<h3>Where do the images on the website come from?</h3>=0A<p>The docu=\nmentary photographs on the NYG&amp;B website are from the Library of Congre=\nss, the New York Public Library, and the New York State Archives. Family ph=\notographs were contributed by NYG&amp;B members, interns, and volunteers ex=\nclusively for use on the NYG&amp;B website; additional information about an=\nd credits for these photographs are available on our <a href=3D\"http://www.=\nflickr.com/photos/nygbs/sets/72157627387490382/\" target=3D\"_blank\">Flickr p=\nage</a>.</p>=0A<h3>When I am in the store and go to checkout, I am asked fo=\nr my customer login even though I am already logged in as a member.=C2=A0 T=\nhen I type in my member username and password and it does not accept them.=\n=C2=A0 Why?</h3>=0A<p>When you go to checkout, you actually land on a page =\nthat belongs to our shopping provider and is outside our website.=C2=A0=C2=\n=A0 If this is your first purchase in the store, please ignore the customer=\n login request and choose the option =E2=80=9CContinue as guest.=E2=80=9D =\n=C2=A0You will be asked to enter your address and contact info, and you wil=\nl be given the option to save this information by creating a customer usern=\name and password for the store.=C2=A0 They can be the same as the ones you =\nuse to log in to our website, or different. =C2=A0</p>=0A<p>*update 12/29/2=\n011 - We have disabled the customer login option for the store.=C2=A0</p>=\n=0A<h3>Why can't I access members-only pages of the website after I visit t=\nhe online store even though I am still=C2=A0 logged in?</h3>=0A<p>If you re=\nturn to the Research &amp; Discover page after visiting the online store, t=\nhere is a glitch that will take you to the non-members version of this page=\n.=C2=A0 To correct this, go the homepage and click the Research &amp; Disco=\nver tab; it will take you to the members version of this page, which is the=\n gateway to the eLibrary and to Research Tools.</p>=0A<h3>How do I update m=\ny membership contact information?</h3>=0A<p>Please send an email to <a href=\n=3D\"mailto:administration@nygbs.org\">membership@nygbs.org</a> with any chan=\nges to your address, telephone, or email address.=C2=A0 Although it is poss=\nible to update your email address when you are logged in, this change will =\nonly appear on your website record and will not automatically be carried ov=\ner to our membership database and eNews mailing list.</p>=0A<h3>You said yo=\nu would send me an email but I did not receive it.</h3>=0A<p>Sometimes we w=\nill reply to an email from a member or send an email to a member's correct =\nemail address and it will go to their Junk Mail folder.=C2=A0 In cases like=\n this, we receive no automatic notification that our email did not reach yo=\nur inbox.=C2=A0 To make sure that you receive all of our email messages, pl=\nease add <a href=3D\"mailto:administration@nygbs.org\">membership@nygbs.org</=\na> and any direct email addresses for NYG&amp;B staff you are in communicat=\nion with to your Safe List.=C2=A0 Recently, emails that we have sent to add=\nresses associated with Prodigy (which include sbc.global.net and snet.net a=\nddresses, among others) have bounced back to us due to a conversion problem=\n between the Prodigy mail server and the Microsoft mail server which transm=\nits our emails through Outlook.=C2=A0 If your email provider uses the Prodi=\ngy server, please contact them and ask them to add our domain (@nygbs.org) =\nto their Safe List.=C2=A0</p>=0A<h3>I did not receive my issues of <em>The =\nNew York Genealogical and Biographical Record</em> or <em>The New York Rese=\narcher </em>=E2=80=93 whom do I contact?</h3>=0A<p>Please contact our membe=\nrship department at <span class=3D\"skype_pnh_print_container\">212-755-8532<=\n/span>, ext. 207 or send email to <a href=3D\"mailto:administration@nygbs.or=\ng\">membership@nygbs.org</a>.=C2=A0 We will mail you a replacement issue and=\n make sure your address is correct for future mailings.</p>=0A<h3>I am not =\nreceiving the monthly eNewsletter. How can I subscribe?</h3>=0A<p>Go to the=\n homepage of this website and enter your email address in the eNews subscri=\nption box. You will automatically be added as a subscriber. Subscriptions a=\nre free. If your email address becomes obsolete, it will be deleted automat=\nically. If you subscribe more than once with the same email address, the sy=\nstem will delete duplicate addresses.</p>=0A<h3>Do you accept advertising i=\nn your publications?</h3>=0A<p>Advertising is welcome in <em>The Record</em=\n> and <em>The New York Researcher</em>.=C2=A0 Learn about our <a href=3D\"/a=\ndvertising\">advertising rates and sizes</a>.</p>=0A<h3>I am interested in s=\nubmitting work for publication in <em>The Record</em> or <em>The Researcher=\n</em> =E2=80=93 whom should I contact?</h3>=0A<p>Please <a href=3D\"/nygbr#w=\nriting\">click here</a> for information on writing for <em>The New York Gene=\nalogical and Biographical Record</em>.</p>=0A<p>If you=E2=80=99re intereste=\nd in submitting work for <em>The New York Researcher</em>, please email <a =\nhref=3D\"mailto:education@nygbs.org\">education@nygbs.org</a> for more inform=\nation.</p>=0A</div>=0A<p>=C2=A0</p>=0A</div></div></div>  </div>=0A=0A  =0A=\n  =0A</div>=0A  </div>=0A</div>=0A Partnership        =\n   \t\t</h1>=0A       =0A                  <div class=3D\"region region-conten=\nt\">=0A    <div id=3D\"block-system-main\" class=3D\"block block-system\">=0A=0A=\n    =0A  <div class=3D\"content\">=0A    <span class=3D\"print-=\nlink\"><span class=3D\"print_html\"><a href=3D\"http://newyorkfamilyhistory.org=\n/print/337\" title=3D\"Display a printer-friendly version of this property=3D\"content:encoded\"><h2>=0A=\n\t<span style=3D\"font-family: times new roman,times,serif;\">Family history h=\nas been and remains one of the most important research pursuits at the New =\nYork Public Library. The NYG&amp;B's gift of its research collections to th=\ne NYPL enriched that <a href=3D\"/librarycollection\">extraordinary resource<=\n/a> and began a new cooperative relationship between the two institutions.=\n=C2=A0 </span></h2>=0A<p>=0A\t<span style=3D\"font-family: arial,helvetica,sa=\nns-serif;\"></span></p>=0A<!--[if gte mso 9]><p><xml><br />=0A <w:WordDocume=\nnt><br />=0A */=0A table.MsoNormalTable=0A\t{mso-style-name:\"Table Normal\";=0A\tmso-tstyl=\ne-rowband-size:0;=0A\tmso-tstyle-colband-size:0;=0A\tmso-style-noshow:yes;=0A=\n\tmso-style-priority:99;=0A\tmso-style-qformat:yes;=0A\tmso-style-parent:\"\";=\n=0A\tmso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;=0A\tmso-para-margin:0in;=0A\tmso-par=\na-margin-bottom:.0001pt;=0A\tmso-pagination:widow-orphan;=0A\tfont-size:11.0p=\nt;=0A\tfont-family:\"Calibri\",\"sans-serif\";=0A\tmso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;=\n=0A\tmso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;=0A\tmso-fareast-font-family:\"Times
