class=3D\"region region-content\">=0A    <div id=3D=\n\"block-system-main\" class=3D\"block block-system\">=0A=0A    =0A  <div class=\n=3D\"content\">=0A    <div id=3D\"node-335\" class=3D\"node node-press-release c=\nlearfix\" about=3D\"/node/335\" typeof=3D\"sioc:Item foaf:Document\">=0A=0A  =0A=\n      =0A  =0A  <div class=3D\"content\">=0A    <span class=3D\"print-link\"><s=\npan class=3D\"print_html\"><a href=3D\"http://newyorkfamilyhistory.org/print/3=\n35\" title=3D\"Display a printer-friendly version of this page.\" class=3D\"pri=\nnt-page\" onclick=3D\"window.open(this.href); return false\" rel=3D\"nofollow\">=\n<img class=3D\"print-icon print-icon-margin\" typeof=3D\"foaf:Image\" src=3D\"ht=\ntp://newyorkfamilyhistory.org/sites/all/modules/print/icons/print_icon.gif\"=\n alt=3D\"Printer-friendly version\" title=3D\"Printer-friendly version\" />Prin=\nter-friendly version</a></span></span><div class=3D\"field field-name-body f=\nield-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden\"><div class=3D\"field-items\">=\n<div class=3D\"field-item even\" property=3D\"content:encoded\"><p>=0A\t<img alt=\n=3D\"\" src=3D\"/sites/default/files/images/df.png\" style=3D\"width: 238px; hei=\nght: 334px; float: right;\" /></p>=0A<p>=0A\t<strong>NEW YORK, NY, November 1=\n1, 2010</strong><strong>.</strong> The New York Genealogical and Biographic=\nal Society is pleased to announce the publication of <em>An Armory of Ameri=\ncan Families of Dutch Descent.</em>=C2=A0 This book gathers together for th=\ne first time all 36 articles on the heraldry of Dutch colonial families wri=\ntten by William J. Hoffman, the pre-eminent authority on the subject, and p=\nreviously published in the <em>New York Genealogical and Biographical Recor=\nd </em>along with his final article which appeared in the<em> New England H=\nistorical and Genealogical Register.=C2=A0 </em>Edited by Francis J. Sypher=\n, Jr., who has provided an introduction and an armorial index, this is an e=\nssential reference for anyone interested in the subject. =C2=A0</p>=0A<p>=\n=0A\tThe book was published on a subscription basis, and a small overrun has=\n been printed in order to accommodate anticipated interest in this definiti=\nve volume.=C2=A0 The text is accompanied by numerous illustrations of arms,=\n with detailed source references that provide both validation and opportuni=\nty for further research.=C2=A0 A limited number of books are available for =\npurchase at a cost of $90, which includes $5 for shipping and handling.=C2=\n=A0 The book may be purchased online at <a href=3D\"http://www.newyorkfamily=\nhistory.org/\">www.newyorkfamilyhistory.org</a> or by calling (212) 755-8532=\n, ext. 208.</p>=0A<p>=0A\t<strong>About the NYG&amp;B</strong></p>=0A<p>=0A\t=\nThe New York Genealogical and Biographical Society has been a primary resou=\nrce for research on New York families since 1869. =C2=A0The NYG&amp;B seeks=\n to advance genealogical scholarship and enhance the capabilities of both n=\new and experienced researchers of family history through a rich schedule of=\n programs, workshops, and repository tours; through its quarterly scholarly=\n journal <em>The NYG&amp;B Record </em>and its quarterly review <em>The New=\n York Researcher</em>; and through an E-Library of unique digital material =\non its website <a href=3D\"http://www.newyorkfamilyhistory.org/\">www.newyork=\nfamilyhistory.org</a>.</p>=0A<div>=0A\t<strong>Contact:</strong></div>=0A<di=\nv>=0A\tMcKelden Smith, President</div>=0A<div>=0A\tNew York Genealogical and =\nBiographical Society</div>=0A<div>=0A\t<a href=3D\"mailto:msmith@nygbs.org\">m=\nsmith@nygbs.org</a></div>=0A<div>=0A\t212-755-8532 x204</div>=0A</div></div>=\n</div>  </div>=0A=0A  =0A  =0A</div>=0A  </div>=0A</div>=0A  </div>=0A     =\n </article>=0A    </div>=0A    <footer>=0A      <nav>=0A        <ul>=0A    =\n      <li><a href=3D\"/privacy\">Privacy</a></li>=0A          <li><a href=3D\"=\n/service-terms\">Terms of Service</a></li>=0A          <li><a href=3D\"/adver=\ntising\">Advertising</a></li>=0A          <li><a href=3D\"/press\">Press Room<=\n/a></li>=0A          <li><a href=3D\"http://www.ironpaper.com\">Web Design</a=\n></li>=0A        </ul>=0A        <a href=3D\"http://www.facebook.com/pages/T=\nhe-New-York-Genealogical-Biographical-Society/166498443372313\" rel=3D\"nofol=\nlow\"  target=3D\"_blank\"><img src=3D\"/sites/all/themes/nygbs/images/content-=\nimg/icon-facebook.png\" alt=3D\"Facebook page\"  border=3D\"0\" /></a>=0A       =\n     <a href=3D\"http://twitter.com/#!/nyfamilyhistory\" rel=3D\"nofollow\" tar=\nget=3D\"_blank\"><img src=3D\"/sites/all/themes/nygbs/images/content-img/icon-=\ntwitter.png\" alt=3D\"Twitter page\"  border=3D\"0\" /></a>=0A            <a hre=\nf=3D\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/nygbs/\" rel=3D\"nofollow\"  target=3D\"_blan=\nk\"><img src=3D\"/sites/all/themes/nygbs/images/content-img/icon-flickr.png\" =\nalt=3D\"Flickr page\"  border=3D\"0\" /></a>=0A      </nav>=0A     <div id=3D\"c=\nopyright\">=0A        New York Genealogical &amp;     =0A                =0A      </aside>=0A            <article class=3D\"\"=\n>      =0A                =0A         <h1 class=3D\"title\" id=3D\"page-title\">=\n=0A                      John Colletta to Lead Full Day Genealogical Worksh=\nop           \t\t</h1>=0A       =0A                  <div class=3D\"region reg=\nion-content\">=0A    <div id=3D\"block-system-main\" class=3D\"block block-syst=\nem\">=0A=0A    =0A  <div class=3D\"content\">=0A    <div id=3D\"node-333\" class=\n=3D\"node node-press-release clearfix\" about=3D\"/node/333\" typeof=3D\"sioc:It=\nem foaf:Document\">=0A=0A  =0A      =0A  =0A  <div class=3D\"content\">=0A    =\n<span class=3D\"print-link\"><span class=3D\"print_html\"><a href=3D\"http://new=\nyorkfamilyhistory.org/print/333\" title=3D\"Display a printer-friendly versio=\nn of this page.\" class=3D\"print-page\" onclick=3D\"window.open(this.href); re=\nturn false\" rel=3D\"nofollow\"><img class=3D\"print-icon title=3D\"Pri=\nnter-friendly version\" />Printer-friendly version</a></span></span><div cla=\nss=3D\"field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden=\n\"><div class=3D\"field-items\"><div class=3D\"field-item even\" property=3D\"con=\ntent:encoded\"><p>=0A\t<strong>NEW YORK, NY, October 7, 2010</strong><strong>=\n.</strong> On Saturday, November 6<sup>th</sup>, the New York Genealogical =\nand Biographical Society will present internationally known genealogist and=\n author John Colletta, Ph.D. in a full-day program at the New York Public L=\nibrary=E2=80=99s Stephen A. Schwarzman Building, Fifth Avenue at 42nd Stree=\nt, New York, NY.=C2=A0 Entertaining, knowledgeable and experienced, Dr. Col=\nletta is based in Washington, D.C., where for 20 years he conducted worksho=\nps for the National Archives and taught courses for the Smithsonian Institu=\ntion.=C2=A0 Today he lectures nationally and is a faculty member of the Ins=\ntitute of Genealogy and Historical Research at Samford University and the S=\nalt Lake Institute of Genealogy.=C2=A0 His publications include the books <=\nem>They Came in Ships: A Guide to Finding Your Immigrant Ancestor's Arrival=\n Records </em>and <em>Finding Italian Roots: The Complete Guide for America=\nns, </em>as well as numerous how-to articles.=C2=A0</p>=0A<p>=0A\tDr. Collet=\nta will give four lectures on the following topics: (1.) Passenger Arrival =\nRecords (1820-1950s) =E2=80=93 Advanced Problem Solving; (2.) Naturalizatio=\nn Records (1790-1920s) =E2=80=93 Advanced Problem Solving; (3.) Turning Bio=\ngraphical Facts into Real Life Events: How to Build Historical Context, and=\n (4.) Breaking Through Brick Walls: Use Your HEAD.=C2=A0 This is a wonderfu=\nl opportunity for researchers of all levels to strengthen their skills and =\nknowledge and to learn from one of the country=E2=80=99s most respected gen=\nealogists.=C2=A0 Dr. Colletta describes his goal as =E2=80=9Cto help family=\n historians optimize their efforts to uncover and write the stories of thei=\nr forebears, and to enjoy all along the way the pleasure and humor of the j=\nourney. =E2=80=9C</p>=0A<p>=0A\tThe program begins at 10:00 a.m. at the NYPL=\n=E2=80=99s South Court Auditorium and will end by 4:30 p.m with a break for=\n lunch on-your-own.=C2=A0 Registration for NYG&amp;B members is $60, non-me=\nmbers is $90.=C2=A0 <a href=3D\"http://newyorkfamilyhistory.myshopify.com/co=\nllections/events\">Register online.</a>=C2=A0 For additional information, co=\nntact Lauren Maehrlein, Director of Education, at 212-755-8532, ext. 211, o=\nr by e-mailing <a href=3D\"mailto:education@nygbs.org\">education@nygbs.org</=\na>.</p>=0A<p>=0A\t<strong>About the NYG&amp;B</strong></p>=0A<p>=0A\tThe New =\nYork Genealogical and Biographical Society has been a primary resource for =\nresearch on New York families since 1869. =C2=A0The NYG&amp;B seeks to adva=\nnce genealogical scholarship and enhance the capabilities of both new and e=\nxperienced researchers of family history through a rich schedule of program=\ns, workshops, and repository tours; through its quarterly scholarly journal=\n <em>The NYG&amp;B Record </em>and its quarterly review <em>The New York Re=\nsearcher</em>; and through an E-Library of unique digital material on its w=\nebsite <a href=3D\"http://www.newyorkfamilyhistory.org/\">www.newyorkfamilyhi=\nstory.org</a>.</p>=0A<div>=0A\t<strong>Media Contact</strong></div>=0A<div>=\n=0A\tMcKelden Smith,     =0A                =0A      </aside>=0A            <arti=\ncle class=3D\"\">      =0A                =0A         <h1 class=3D\"title\" id=\n=3D\"page-title\">=0A                      The New York Genealogical and Biog=\nraphical Society Announces New Digital Resources for its Members           =\n\t\t</h1>=0A       =0A                  <div class=3D\"region region-content\">=\n=0A    <div id=3D\"block-system-main\" class=3D\"block block-system\">=0A=0A    =\n=0A  <div class=3D\"content\">=0A    <div id=3D\"node-331\" class=3D\"node node-=\npress-release clearfix\" about=3D\"/node/331\" typeof=3D\"sioc:Item foaf:Docume=\nnt\">=0A=0A  =0A      =0A  =0A  <div class=3D\"content\">=0A    <span class=3D=\n\"print-link\"><span class=3D\"print_html\"><a href=3D\"http://newyorkfamilyhist=\nory.org/print/331\" title=3D\"Display a printer-friendly version of this page=\n.\" class=3D\"print-page\" onclick=3D\"window.open(this.href); return false\" re=\nl=3D\"nofollow\"><img class=3D\"print-icon print-icon-margin\" typeof=3D\"foaf:I=\nmage\" src=3D\"http://newyorkfamilyhistory.org/sites/all/modules/print/icons/=\nprint_icon.gif\" alt=3D\"Printer-friendly version\" title=3D\"Printer-friendly =\nversion\" />Printer-friendly version</a></span></span><div class=3D\"field fi=\neld-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden\"><div class=\n=3D\"field-items\"><div class=3D\"field-item even\" property=3D\"content:encoded=\n\"><p>=0A\t<strong>NEW YORK, NY, October 1, 2010</strong><strong>.</strong> T=\nhe New York Genealogical and Biographical Society is pleased to announce th=\nat all issues of the NYG&amp;B Record are now accessible online to the Soci=\nety=E2=80=99s members. The entire run of the NYG&amp;B Record comprises 563=\n issues at this writing and forms the largest single collection of publishe=\nd material on families that lived in New York State. The collection is ever=\ny-word searchable and is accompanied by a new surname search engine based o=\nn an index to more than 1,000,000 names from the pages of the Record. Origi=\nnally created by Jean Worden, the search engine will simultaneously search =\nevery issue from 1870-2009 and will be updated every October when the year=\n=E2=80=99s annual index is released.</p>=0A<p>\tContinuously published since=\n 1870, the NYG&amp;B Record is the second oldest genealogical journal in th=\ne country and one of the most distinguished. Published quarterly, it concen=\ntrates on people and places within New York City, State, and region and fea=\ntures compiled genealogies, solutions to problems, and unique source materi=\nal. Access to the digital version of the Record is available exclusively to=\n NYG&amp;B members through the Society=E2=80=99s growing E-Library of uniqu=\ne material on its website, <a href=3D\"http://www.newyorkfamilyhistory.org\">=\nwww.newyorkfamilyhistory.org</a>.</p>=0A<p>\t<strong>Other New Content</stro=\nng></p>=0A<p>\tExpanding the digital content available to NYG&amp;B members =\nis one of the Society=E2=80=99s foremost goals. Book one of the 1855 New Yo=\nrk State Census for Ward 17 of New York City, including an every name index=\n was recently posted to the E-Library. Ward 17 was often the first home of =\nnew immigrants who arrived in the middle of the 19th century. The original =\ncensus returns were damaged by fire and sat unused for many years. Thanks t=\no an extraordinary effort by NYG&amp;B volunteers and interns these records=\n are now being made available. The remaining books will be posted once the =\nindexing is complete. Also in progress is the posting of more than 500 biog=\nraphical sketches of NYG&amp;B members from the first half of the 20th cent=\nury. Personally completed by each member as part of their application to th=\ne Society, these biographies contain exceptional firsthand narratives, fami=\nly trees, and ephemera.</p>=0A<p>\t<strong>About the NYG&amp;B</strong></p>=\n=0A<p>\tThe New York Genealogical and Biographical Society has been a primar=\ny resource for research on New York families since 1869. The NYG&amp;B seek=\ns to advance genealogical scholarship and enhance the capabilities of both =\nnew and experienced researchers of family history through a rich schedule o=\nf programs, workshops, and repository tours; through its quarterly scholarl=\ny journal The NYG&amp;B Record and its quarterly review The New York Resear=\ncher; and through an E-Library of unique digital material on its website <a=\n href=3D\"http://www.newyorkfamilyhistory.org\">www.newyorkfamilyhistory.org<=\n/a>.</p>=0A<div>=0A\t<strong>Contact:</strong></div>=0A<div>=0A\tMcKelden Smi=\nth, President</div>=0A<div>=0A\tNew York Genealogical and Biographical Socie=\nty</div>=0A<div>=0A\t<a href=3D\"mailto:msmith@nygbs.org\">msmith@nygbs.org</a=\n></div>=0A<div>=0A\t212-755-8532 x204</div>=0A</div></div></div>  </div>=0A=\n=0A  =0A  =0A</div>=0A  </div>=0A</div>=0A  </div>=0A      </article>=0A   =\n </div>=0A    <footer>=0A      <nav>=0A        <ul>=0A          <li><a href=\n=3D\"/privacy\">Privacy</a></li>=0A          <li><a href=3D\"/service-terms\">T=\nerms of Service</a></li>=0A          <li><a href=3D\"/advertising\">Advertisi=\nng</a></li>=0A          <li><a href=3D\"/press\">Press Room</a></li>=0A      =\n    <li><a href=3D\"http://www.ironpaper.com\">Web Design</a></li>=0A        =\n</ul>=0A        <a href=3D\"http://www.facebook.com/pages/The-New-York-Genea=\nlogical-Biographical-Society/166498443372313\" rel=3D\"nofollow\"  target=3D\"_=\nblank\"><img src=3D\"/sites/all/themes/nygbs/images/content-img/icon-facebook=\n.png\" alt=3D\"Facebook page\"  border=3D\"0\" /></a>=0A            <a href=3D\"h=\nttp://twitter.com/#!/nyfamilyhistory\" rel=3D\"nofollow\" target=3D\"_blank\"><i=\nmg src=3D\"/sites/all/themes/nygbs/images/content-img/icon-twitter.png\" alt=\n=3D\"Twitter page\"  border=3D\"0\" /></a>=0A            <a href=3D\"http://www.=\nflickr.com/photos/nygbs/\" rel=3D\"nofollow\"  target=3D\"_blank\"><img src=3D\"/=\nsites/all/themes/nygbs/images/content-img/icon-flickr.png\" alt=3D\"Flickr pa=\nge\"  border=3D\"0\" /></a>=0A      </nav>=0A     <div id=3D\"copyright\">=0A   =\n     New York Genealogical &amp;
